WEBVTT

01:13.657 --> 01:16.288
Nick, this was a tragedy,
but it's not why we're here.

01:16.704 --> 01:18.735
What, are we fighting the weather now?

01:18.829 --> 01:21.572
Locals say the cyclone had a face.

01:21.665 --> 01:24.001
People see things
when they're under stress.

01:24.418 --> 01:27.319
That does not mean that
this is the start to some other...

01:27.321 --> 01:28.491
big world-ending...

01:34.344 --> 01:35.344
Who are you?

01:40.726 --> 01:42.309
You don't want any part of this.

02:58.470 --> 03:00.632
<i>Gone but not forgotten.</i>

03:00.722 --> 03:02.805
<i>Thanks to Kenneth Lim
and Vihaan Ramamurthy</i>

03:02.891 --> 03:04.928
<i>for their help
with that touching video tribute.</i>

03:05.018 --> 03:07.254
<i>This year has been
nothing short of...</i>

03:07.256 --> 03:08.367
<i>♪♪♪♪ is crazy.</i>

03:08.738 --> 03:09.732
<i>It's insane.</i>

03:09.826 --> 03:10.690
<i>Jason.
What?</i>

03:10.691 --> 03:11.561
<i>No swearing.</i>

03:12.067 --> 03:13.808
<i>It's the last day of school. We're good.</i>

03:14.986 --> 03:15.986
<i>Historic.</i>

03:16.293 --> 03:19.412
<i>Over five years ago,
half of all life in the universe,</i>

03:19.498 --> 03:23.173
<i>including our own Midtown High,
was wiped from existence.</i>

03:23.787 --> 03:26.529
<i>But then eight months ago,
a band of brave heroes,</i>

03:26.531 --> 03:27.531
<i>brought us back.</i>

03:29.793 --> 03:31.580
<i>They called it the Blip.</i>

03:31.755 --> 03:34.338
<i>Those of us who Blipped away
came back the same age,</i>

03:34.537 --> 03:38.621
<i>But our classmates that didn't Blip
had grown five years older.</i>

03:39.010 --> 03:41.396
<i>My little brother is
now older than me.</i>

03:41.398 --> 03:42.648
<i>Yeah, it's math.</i>

03:43.266 --> 03:46.136
<i>And even though we had Blipped away
halfway through the school year</i>

03:46.138 --> 03:48.434
<i>and had already taken midterms,</i>

03:48.520 --> 03:51.183
<i>the school made us start the whole year
over from the beginning.</i>

03:51.377 --> 03:52.510
<i>It's totally unfair.</i>

03:53.024 --> 03:53.885
<i>It's not right.</i>

03:54.234 --> 03:55.034
<i>Tigers,</i>

03:55.568 --> 03:57.368
<i>it's been a long, dramatic,</i>

03:57.557 --> 03:59.283
<i>somewhat confusing road.</i>

03:59.832 --> 04:01.690
<i>As we draw this year to a close,</i>

04:01.783 --> 04:03.991
<i>it's time to move on.</i>

04:05.078 --> 04:07.126
<i>To a new phase of our lives.</i>

04:07.191 --> 04:08.308
<i>Pray nothing crazy happens again</i>

04:08.310 --> 04:10.184
<i>because are the Avengers even
a thing anymore?</i>

04:10.417 --> 04:11.722
<i>Does anyone even have a plan?</i>

04:12.481 --> 04:13.355
I have a plan.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.987
Ok, first, I'm gonna sit
next to MJ on the flight.

04:16.548 --> 04:18.398
Second, I'm gonna buy
a dual-headphone adapter,

04:18.550 --> 04:20.357
and watch movies with her
the whole time.

04:20.554 --> 04:21.054
Ok.

04:21.125 --> 04:22.594
Three, when we go to Venice.

04:22.681 --> 04:24.857
Venice is famous for making stuff
out of glass, right?

04:24.859 --> 04:26.047
True.
So I'm gonna buy her,

04:26.049 --> 04:28.889
a black dahlia necklace because
her favorite flower is the black dahlia...

04:29.060 --> 04:30.602
because of, well...
The murder.

04:30.654 --> 04:32.777
The murder.
Four, when we go to Paris,

04:32.779 --> 04:34.627
I'm gonna take her to the top
of the Eiffel Tower,

04:34.837 --> 04:35.997
give her the necklace.

04:36.335 --> 04:38.332
Then, five, I'm gonna tell her how I feel.

04:39.873 --> 04:41.699
And then six,
hopefully she tells me,

04:41.772 --> 04:42.797
she feels the same way.

04:43.314 --> 04:44.400
Don't forget step seven.

04:44.409 --> 04:45.564
Step seven?

04:45.566 --> 04:46.495
Don't do any of that.

04:48.007 --> 04:48.625
Why?

04:48.765 --> 04:50.982
Because we're gonna be
bachelors in Europe, Peter.

04:50.984 --> 04:51.861
Ned.
Look.

04:51.994 --> 04:53.803
I may not know much
but I do know this.

04:54.252 --> 04:56.619
Europeans love Americans.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.504
Really?
And, more than half of them are women.

04:59.950 --> 05:01.173
Ok. Sure.

05:01.259 --> 05:01.762
But...

05:02.472 --> 05:04.260
I really like MJ, man, ok?

05:04.262 --> 05:05.283
She's awesome,

05:05.285 --> 05:07.196
she's super funny
in a kind of dark way.

05:07.383 --> 05:08.845
And sometimes I catch her
looking at me,

05:08.847 --> 05:09.762
I feel like I've stood up...

05:09.851 --> 05:11.230
Wait. She's coming.
Just don't say anything.

05:11.235 --> 05:12.063
What up, dorks?

05:12.250 --> 05:13.512
Excited about the science trip?

05:13.514 --> 05:15.953
Hey, yeah, we're just
talking about the trip.

05:15.955 --> 05:17.111
Yeah, and Peter's plan.

05:17.113 --> 05:18.316
You have a plan?

05:18.902 --> 05:19.785
I don't...

05:20.368 --> 05:21.480
I don't have a plan.

05:22.470 --> 05:25.211
No, he's just gonna collect tiny spoons
when we're traveling to other countries.

05:26.187 --> 05:27.678
Like... like a grandmother?

05:28.500 --> 05:31.064
I'm not collecting tiny spoons.
He's collecting tiny spoons.

05:31.472 --> 05:32.810
Ok, well...

05:33.875 --> 05:35.800
that was a real roller coaster.

05:36.665 --> 05:37.655
By the way, travel tip.

05:37.657 --> 05:39.752
You should probably download a VPN
on your phone,

05:39.754 --> 05:42.087
just so the government
can't track you while we're abroad.

05:42.217 --> 05:43.102
Smart.

05:43.993 --> 05:44.713
Will do.

05:50.263 --> 05:52.763
Dude, I think that went really great.

05:55.337 --> 05:57.528
<i>When, when I Blipped back
to my apartment,</i>

05:57.530 --> 06:00.085
<i>the family that was living there
was very confused.</i>

06:00.560 --> 06:02.798
<i>The wife thought that
I was a mistress.</i>

06:03.154 --> 06:05.385
<i>The grandma thought
that I was a ghost.</i>

06:05.387 --> 06:07.106
<i>It was... It was really a mess.</i>

06:07.367 --> 06:09.063
<i>Thank you all for coming out</i>

06:09.065 --> 06:11.527
<i>to support those who have been
displaced by the Blip.</i>

06:11.621 --> 06:14.105
<i>And of course,
thanks to our very own,</i>

06:14.364 --> 06:15.668
<i>Spider-Man!</i>

06:26.300 --> 06:28.366
<i>Thank you Miss Parker,
for having me.</i>

06:29.464 --> 06:31.922
<i>And thank you, you guys,
for having me.</i>

06:34.532 --> 06:35.898
<i>And thank you, Spider-Man.</i>

06:35.900 --> 06:38.214
<i>He'll be right back out
to take photos and...</i>

06:38.403 --> 06:39.661
<i>videos. Thank you!</i>

06:45.640 --> 06:47.392
That was amazing.
That was great.

06:47.680 --> 06:49.317
That was so cool.
I was so nervous.

06:49.364 --> 06:51.163
Sorry, I was a little stiff.
I felt like I wasn't in the pocket.

06:51.262 --> 06:52.130
No, I thought you did great.

06:52.218 --> 06:54.222
Yeah, I actually thought
you were a little stiff.

06:55.172 --> 06:56.743
Yeah, I felt that too. I felt that too.

06:56.913 --> 06:58.168
It's fine, it's fine, it's fine.
Ok.

06:58.557 --> 06:59.792
Did you get your passport?
Yeah.

06:59.794 --> 07:01.074
Mini toothpaste?
Yeah, I did.

07:02.987 --> 07:04.216
Hey, sorry I'm late.

07:05.044 --> 07:06.444
Happy. Hey.

07:06.446 --> 07:07.547
You look lovely.

07:07.636 --> 07:08.704
Thanks. You too.

07:08.939 --> 07:09.594
Thank you.

07:09.874 --> 07:11.911
New dress?
Yeah, yes, it is.

07:12.891 --> 07:13.971
It's a new beard.

07:13.973 --> 07:15.100
It's my... My Blip beard.

07:15.334 --> 07:16.847
I grew it in the Blip.

07:17.395 --> 07:18.636
It's a Blip beard.

07:18.884 --> 07:20.091
I see. Yeah.

07:20.360 --> 07:21.603
Yeah, anyway, so...

07:21.605 --> 07:23.508
the reason I'm late is because
this was misplaced at the office.

07:23.510 --> 07:25.062
Can you believe it?
Because it's enormous.

07:25.196 --> 07:26.445
I mean not the amount, the size.

07:26.495 --> 07:27.759
So the amount's nice, too.

07:28.458 --> 07:30.267
They're very generous.
Pepper Potts said,

07:30.269 --> 07:31.810
sorry she couldn't be here.
Yeah. Thank you.

07:32.202 --> 07:34.085
I think I'm gonna go change the...

07:34.357 --> 07:36.126
Sterno under the vegan lasagne.

07:37.364 --> 07:38.385
Spider-Man,

07:38.488 --> 07:39.445
go shake hands.

07:39.646 --> 07:40.512
Will do.

07:45.683 --> 07:46.799
What just happened?

07:47.425 --> 07:48.247
Heads up,

07:48.903 --> 07:49.866
Nick Fury's calling you.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.517
Nick Fury's gonna call me?
Yeah.

07:51.518 --> 07:52.101
Why?

07:52.257 --> 07:54.862
Why? Because he probably
has some hero stuff for you to do.

07:55.057 --> 07:57.016
You're a superhero.
He calls superheroes.

07:57.065 --> 08:00.263
Well I mean, if it was that important,
he'd probably call someone else, not me.

08:01.523 --> 08:02.559
Apparently not.

08:06.714 --> 08:08.453
No caller ID. That's him.

08:08.455 --> 08:09.779
I don't really wanna talk to Fury.

08:09.781 --> 08:10.813
Answer the phone.
Why?

08:10.837 --> 08:13.248
Because if you don't talk to him,
than I have to talk and I don't want to him.

08:13.250 --> 08:15.530
But why don't you want to talk to him?
Because I'm scared. Just answer the phone.

08:16.986 --> 08:18.862
You sent Nick Fury to voicemail?
Yeah.

08:18.916 --> 08:20.071
You don't send Fury to voicemail.

08:20.073 --> 08:21.423
Did you hear that?
They're calling me.

08:21.427 --> 08:23.377
It's.. I got to go. I got to go.
You got to talk to him.

08:23.384 --> 08:26.190
I'm gonna call him. I promise you,
I'm gonna call him. I will.

08:26.245 --> 08:27.964
You do not ghost Nick Fury.

08:27.966 --> 08:29.753
I promise you, I'll call him.

08:31.550 --> 08:32.565
After my trip.

08:33.275 --> 08:34.275
Hey!

08:35.181 --> 08:36.051
Yeah, hi...

08:36.568 --> 08:37.865
No, no, he's not ghosting you.

08:40.812 --> 08:42.678
Ok. Ok, one question at a time.

08:42.772 --> 08:45.342
Are you the head Avenger?
Are you the head Avenger now?

08:45.722 --> 08:46.722
No, I'm not.

08:46.724 --> 08:48.886
If the aliens come back,
what are you gonna do?

08:48.987 --> 08:50.667
If the aliens come back,
what are you gonna do?

08:51.114 --> 08:52.980
Does anyone have
any neighborhood questions?

08:54.223 --> 08:55.625
Sean Winford, Queens Tribune.

08:55.771 --> 08:57.566
What it is like to take over
for Tony Stark?

08:57.755 --> 08:59.212
Those are some big shoes to fill.

09:02.877 --> 09:03.623
I'm...

09:04.476 --> 09:06.429
I'm gonna go. Thanks so much,
everyone for coming.

09:47.170 --> 09:47.942
Ok.

09:54.177 --> 09:55.177
Hungry?

09:57.506 --> 09:58.564
So sorry.

09:59.174 --> 10:01.267
I thought you could sense that with your...

10:01.779 --> 10:02.384
Peter-tingle.

10:02.623 --> 10:04.810
Please do not start calling it
my Peter-tingle.

10:05.035 --> 10:05.888
So what's up?

10:05.890 --> 10:07.935
You can dodge bullets but not bananas?

10:08.242 --> 10:10.056
No, I just really need this vacation.

10:10.058 --> 10:11.184
I need a break.

10:12.849 --> 10:13.784
You deserve it.

10:16.362 --> 10:17.117
Yeah.

10:18.096 --> 10:18.988
You know what?

10:20.107 --> 10:21.889
You should pack your suit,
just in case.

10:22.188 --> 10:23.289
I have a tingle about it.

10:24.261 --> 10:26.209
Please stop saying tingle, May.

10:28.962 --> 10:29.872
No.

10:36.511 --> 10:37.969
No. No, I'm not.

10:43.480 --> 10:44.417
Awasome.
Yeah!

10:52.545 --> 10:54.639
Do you want the first shift
or the second? I could take either.

10:55.029 --> 10:57.066
Give me the third shift.
I took an Ambien.

10:57.453 --> 10:58.938
I can't chaperone these kids alone.

10:58.940 --> 10:59.992
Yo, Parker.

11:00.248 --> 11:03.116
This is called an airplane.
It's like the buses you're used to,

11:03.121 --> 11:06.555
except it flies over the poor neighborhoods
instead of driving through them.

11:06.869 --> 11:07.586
Ma'am?

11:08.466 --> 11:11.748
He Blipped, so technically,
he's 16, not 21.

11:12.046 --> 11:12.978
I'll take that.

11:13.337 --> 11:15.795
She's lying. I don't even know this girl.

11:18.444 --> 11:19.713
Classic MJ, right?

11:22.148 --> 11:23.598
Did you know Brad was coming?

11:24.457 --> 11:26.179
It... It's so weird.

11:26.861 --> 11:29.601
One day, he's that little kid who cried
and got nosebleeds all the time,

11:29.603 --> 11:31.272
and suddenly, we Blip back,

11:31.294 --> 11:33.820
and he's totally
ripped and super nice

11:33.822 --> 11:35.004
and all these girls are after him.

11:35.069 --> 11:38.403
Not all the girls are after him.
No, man, they're all after him.

11:38.489 --> 11:39.480
Yeah. Here.

11:40.161 --> 11:42.529
Anyway, on to more important things.

11:42.619 --> 11:43.992
It's a nine-hour flight.

11:43.994 --> 11:45.705
We can play Beast Slayers
the whole time.

11:46.164 --> 11:47.450
Are you excited?

11:48.583 --> 11:50.165
I need your help to sit next to MJ.

11:52.063 --> 11:54.071
Seriously?
Yes, seriously.

11:54.073 --> 11:57.099
What about our plan?
American bachelors in Europe.

11:57.101 --> 11:59.889
That's your plan. That's a solo plan.
Come on, this is my plan.

12:03.225 --> 12:04.145
Please.

12:08.324 --> 12:09.347
Hey, guys.

12:10.146 --> 12:14.231
There's an old lady in front of us
wearing a crazy amount of perfume,

12:14.317 --> 12:17.788
and it's kind of setting off
Peter's allergies.

12:18.824 --> 12:20.052
You know Betty, if you could just...

12:20.396 --> 12:21.866
switch seats with him that would be...

12:21.868 --> 12:23.139
He's allergic to perfume?

12:24.355 --> 12:25.972
Yeah, yeah, because...

12:26.120 --> 12:27.736
It makes his eyes water,

12:27.937 --> 12:30.118
and he can't really...
You said Peter has a perfume allergy?

12:31.376 --> 12:33.814
I'll tell you from experience,
perfume allergies are no joke.

12:34.102 --> 12:35.668
I can feel hives breaking out already.

12:35.912 --> 12:36.968
MJ, stand up.

12:37.246 --> 12:40.397
Ned, take MJ's spot.
MJ, you take my spot.

12:41.041 --> 12:42.584
Peter, come with me.
Let's get you out of there.

12:42.666 --> 12:44.293
Sorry.
Zach and Sebastian,

12:44.310 --> 12:46.032
you take Ned and Peter's seats.
That's alright.

12:46.808 --> 12:49.092
Ned, thanks for bringing this
to my attention.

12:49.389 --> 12:52.670
Your safety is my responsibility.
And Mr. Dell's, but he's...

12:53.543 --> 12:55.626
I got it for now. Let's go, Peter!

12:56.150 --> 12:57.150
Let's go!

13:04.022 --> 13:04.810
Yeah,

13:05.241 --> 13:07.459
I have a small bladder,
so I took the aisle.

13:10.328 --> 13:13.036
So did you want to play Beast Slayer?

13:13.131 --> 13:13.918
Nope.

13:15.281 --> 13:17.512
Have you ever played
any kind of PC game or...?

13:17.514 --> 13:17.930
No.
Got it.

13:20.304 --> 13:22.347
Did I tell you how my wife
pretended to Blip out?

13:24.013 --> 13:25.921
Turns out, she ran off
with a guy in her hiking group.

13:26.723 --> 13:28.180
We had a fake funeral
for her and everything.

13:28.182 --> 13:29.465
Well, the funeral was real...

13:29.596 --> 13:31.416
because I thought she was really dead.

13:31.436 --> 13:32.472
Did you wanna see the video?

13:32.562 --> 13:35.219
I got a dual-headphone adapter
if you want to watch a movie.

13:35.565 --> 13:36.898
Only if it's depressing.

13:36.900 --> 13:38.013
Or hilarious.

13:38.151 --> 13:39.712
You have a dual-headphone adapter.

13:40.254 --> 13:41.423
We can watch together.

13:41.612 --> 13:44.605
<i>Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen,
this is your captain speaking.</i>

13:44.676 --> 13:48.701
<i>Our flight time today will be eight hours
and 49 minutes to Venice, Italy.</i>

14:55.589 --> 14:58.304
Hey man, did you see Brad and MJ
on the plane?

14:58.306 --> 15:00.309
They were watching movies
and laughing the entire time.

15:00.698 --> 15:02.157
Dude, don't worry, ok?

15:02.159 --> 15:03.947
I'm sure that's nothing.
Hey, babe.

15:04.330 --> 15:05.725
Can you hold this for me, please?

15:05.761 --> 15:07.468
Yeah, of course.
Thanks.

15:16.165 --> 15:17.165
What was that?

15:18.489 --> 15:18.990
Well,

15:19.248 --> 15:21.611
we actually got to talking
on the plane, and it turns out,

15:21.763 --> 15:23.139
we have a lot in common.

15:23.343 --> 15:25.479
So we're boyfriend and girlfriend now.

15:26.195 --> 15:28.626
Whatever happened to being
an American bachelor in Europe?

15:28.804 --> 15:29.464
Peter,

15:29.816 --> 15:31.168
those were the words of a boy.

15:31.606 --> 15:33.972
And that boy met a woman.

15:34.233 --> 15:36.937
A very strong and powerful woman.

15:37.039 --> 15:37.893
And now...

15:38.444 --> 15:39.455
that boy is a man.

15:39.918 --> 15:41.430
Babe?
Coming, babe.

15:47.129 --> 15:49.112
There's nothing in there. I swear.

16:05.802 --> 16:06.825
These, no.

16:16.100 --> 16:17.511
Sorry.

16:18.561 --> 16:20.598
I'm here. Mr. Harrington.
Wait, wait, wait.

16:20.688 --> 16:22.645
I'm here, I'm here.
Thank goodness.

16:56.599 --> 16:57.791
Looks like we're here.

16:58.444 --> 17:00.340
They're doing some
renovations to the place.

17:00.399 --> 17:01.420
Getting some upgrades.

17:02.053 --> 17:02.937
This is trash.

17:02.939 --> 17:04.520
That must be the concierge.
Ok.

17:04.653 --> 17:05.547
Come on, man.

17:06.285 --> 17:07.323
Everyone,

17:07.981 --> 17:09.146
here we are.

17:10.488 --> 17:12.481
Tell me we're not staying here.
Come on in.

17:12.620 --> 17:14.062
This place is sinking.

17:14.532 --> 17:16.353
I think you mean, charming.
It stinks.

17:16.369 --> 17:17.488
Ok, everybody,

17:17.937 --> 17:18.915
drop your bags off.

17:18.917 --> 17:21.369
We're gonna meet
at the da Vinci Museum at 3.

17:21.370 --> 17:22.162
Let's go!

17:22.163 --> 17:23.790
¡Vamonos!
It's andiamo.

17:23.792 --> 17:25.205
Andiamo!
There you go.

17:25.245 --> 17:26.751
When in Rome, do as the Romans do.

17:26.785 --> 17:28.794
When you're in Venice,
your socks get wet.

17:34.524 --> 17:35.836
What's up, Flash Mob?

17:35.838 --> 17:36.959
How you guys doing?

17:36.961 --> 17:38.728
I'm here in St. Marco Polo's...

17:40.785 --> 17:42.450
This is so much fun.
Yeah?

18:05.976 --> 18:08.014
Three, two, one.
Say pizza.

18:08.090 --> 18:09.938
Pizza!
Pizza time!

18:29.528 --> 18:30.848
Buongiorno.
Buongiorno

18:31.665 --> 18:32.176
Hi.

18:33.164 --> 18:34.705
I'm looking for a...

18:35.088 --> 18:36.144
Black flower.

18:45.833 --> 18:46.850
It's perfect.

18:54.861 --> 18:55.848
Boh!

18:57.079 --> 18:57.772
What?

18:58.079 --> 18:58.814
Boh.

18:58.881 --> 19:00.205
The most perfect word in the world.

19:00.207 --> 19:01.848
Italians created it,
and I just discovered it.

19:01.932 --> 19:02.779
What does it mean?

19:02.781 --> 19:04.292
That's the thing,
it can mean a million things.

19:04.300 --> 19:05.808
It could mean,
I don't know. Get out of my face.

19:05.933 --> 19:07.415
I don't know and Get out of my face.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.355
It's the best thing Italy created,
except for maybe espresso.

19:11.285 --> 19:12.741
So you've been drinking espresso.

19:13.093 --> 19:13.530
American.

19:13.621 --> 19:15.827
Hey. German? American.

19:16.595 --> 19:17.513
A rose for you.
Boh.

19:20.763 --> 19:22.150
Boh is my new superpower.

19:22.244 --> 19:23.482
It's like the anti-aloha.

19:23.560 --> 19:24.828
I was born to say this word.

19:25.956 --> 19:27.210
So, what's in the bag?

19:29.931 --> 19:30.376
Boh.

19:31.337 --> 19:32.171
Nice.

19:40.815 --> 19:41.620
Cool.

19:58.364 --> 19:59.364
What was that?

20:22.555 --> 20:24.421
Betty! You ok?
Yeah.

20:25.433 --> 20:26.580
Oh my God!
Come on.

20:27.225 --> 20:28.421
Guys, we got to go!

20:32.440 --> 20:33.647
What is that?
I don't know.

20:33.733 --> 20:35.687
What are you gonna do?
I left my suit in the hotel room.

20:35.689 --> 20:37.366
Why?
Because I'm on vacation, Ned!

20:37.572 --> 20:39.452
Everyone's gonna see my face.
Just get them out of here.

20:39.454 --> 20:40.601
Go!
Just go!

20:50.960 --> 20:51.546
Ned go!

20:54.503 --> 20:55.539
Oh my God.

21:03.763 --> 21:04.763
Come on.

21:18.349 --> 21:19.185
No, you don't.

21:29.789 --> 21:30.696
You ok?

21:30.698 --> 21:31.874
Get out of here. Go!

22:23.557 --> 22:24.402
Excuse me, sir!

22:24.558 --> 22:25.998
I... I can help. Let me help.

22:26.131 --> 22:27.863
I'm really strong, and I'm sticky.

22:27.926 --> 22:29.813
I need to lead it away from the canals.

22:55.694 --> 22:57.097
The da Vinci Museum.

22:57.276 --> 22:58.990
This is why we're
here in Venice.

22:59.120 --> 23:00.110
This is it.

23:00.588 --> 23:01.506
It's closed.

23:01.928 --> 23:03.702
What do you mean it's closed?
Till when?

23:03.716 --> 23:04.572
November.

23:04.800 --> 23:06.376
You didn't check the website?

23:06.669 --> 23:07.793
That's a good idea.

23:22.902 --> 23:23.983
Come on.

23:28.073 --> 23:30.066
Stay low, kids. We'll be safe here.

24:28.968 --> 24:30.334
Who is that guy?

24:30.427 --> 24:32.464
I don't know,
but he's kicking that water's ass.

25:03.669 --> 25:05.911
Yeah! Yeah!

25:21.812 --> 25:23.348
It's aliens. It has to be.

25:23.524 --> 25:25.602
BuzzFeed says there is a sailor
named Morris Bench

25:25.604 --> 25:28.168
who was exposed to an experimental
underwater generator

25:28.170 --> 25:29.394
and got hydro powers.

25:29.651 --> 25:32.403
Yeah, you should definitely believe
everything you read on the Internet.

25:32.746 --> 25:35.159
Spider-Man could take him.
What do you think it is?

25:37.327 --> 25:39.114
You know, being a man of science...

25:40.330 --> 25:41.225
witches.

25:41.665 --> 25:43.596
No, no, no. We wanna stay.
We wanna stay.

25:43.625 --> 25:45.219
It's a good thing I packed your suit?

25:45.553 --> 25:46.811
<i>I can't believe you forgot it.</i>

25:47.217 --> 25:47.914
Yeah.

25:48.165 --> 25:51.198
So who was that guy that you were with?
Was that Mr. Strange?

25:51.339 --> 25:53.891
Doctor Strange, May.
Doctor Strange.

25:54.254 --> 25:55.933
And no, I don't know who that was.

25:56.019 --> 25:56.924
<i>It was a new guy.</i>

25:57.014 --> 25:58.293
I was trying to help him but...
<i>Hey Happy!</i>

25:58.624 --> 25:59.628
That's my lunch.

25:59.630 --> 26:00.427
Don't eat that one.

26:00.517 --> 26:01.471
Happy's there?

26:01.803 --> 26:03.154
Yeah, it's Happy.

26:04.129 --> 26:06.009
He's here. He came by to volunteer.

26:06.102 --> 26:08.060
<i>And he's hanging around the office.</i>

26:08.188 --> 26:09.252
And he wants to say hi.

26:09.254 --> 26:10.740
I don't want... Hi, Peter.

26:11.028 --> 26:12.109
Hey, Happy.

26:13.658 --> 26:16.845
Sorry, I'm working real hard here.
I got to do a... A leaflet drop.

26:17.950 --> 26:20.231
What are you doing?
<i>Glad you're having a good time.</i>

26:20.341 --> 26:22.056
Don't worry,
I'm really taking care of your aunt.

26:25.000 --> 26:26.165
So...

26:26.377 --> 26:27.794
<i>how's the plan going?</i>

26:29.789 --> 26:31.625
There's been setbacks, for sure.

26:31.863 --> 26:34.299
Don't over-think it. It's just trust
your instincts and you'll be fine.

26:34.425 --> 26:35.425
<i>I know. Love you.</i>

26:35.594 --> 26:36.396
Bye.

26:38.726 --> 26:39.842
Who is that guy?

26:40.108 --> 26:42.176
He's like Iron Man and Thor
rolled into one.

26:42.518 --> 26:44.635
He's alright. He's no Spider-Man.

26:44.728 --> 26:46.854
What is it with you and Spider-Man?

26:47.638 --> 26:49.686
What? He's just awesome, ok?

26:49.821 --> 26:53.151
He protects the neighborhood
and you know, he's inspiring.

26:53.153 --> 26:54.798
He inspires me to be a better man.

26:55.364 --> 26:56.629
What's up, dickwad?

26:56.740 --> 26:57.807
Thought you drowned.

27:01.213 --> 27:02.749
Sounds like his name's Mysterio.

27:03.209 --> 27:06.702
L'uomo Del misterio is Italian
for man of mystery.

27:06.704 --> 27:08.392
They don't actually know who he is.

27:08.589 --> 27:09.816
Mysterio.

27:10.963 --> 27:12.295
Cool name.
Cool name.

27:13.882 --> 27:14.882
Babe.
Babe.

27:15.130 --> 27:16.842
So how much of that
did you actually see?

27:17.129 --> 27:18.968
Not much. I was running.

27:19.203 --> 27:20.112
Right. Me too.

27:20.114 --> 27:21.531
I was also running...

27:22.181 --> 27:23.083
away.

27:25.101 --> 27:26.343
So Paris tomorrow.

27:27.291 --> 27:28.584
Go to the Eiffel Tower.

27:29.295 --> 27:30.284
Should be great.

27:30.286 --> 27:33.053
Yeah, I read it was secretly built
as a mind-control antenna

27:33.055 --> 27:34.671
to create an army of the insane.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.302
Which is why it's my favorite
destination on the whole trip.

27:41.493 --> 27:43.450
What are you gonna do about
the water monster?

27:44.098 --> 27:45.098
Nothing.

27:45.122 --> 27:45.970
It's dead.

27:45.972 --> 27:47.942
And besides, that
Mysterio guy's all over it.

27:48.208 --> 27:50.040
Look, I just wanna
spend some time with MJ.

27:50.042 --> 27:51.439
We were talking about Paris and...

27:51.997 --> 27:53.207
I think she really likes me.

27:53.380 --> 27:54.380
That's nice.

27:54.846 --> 27:56.543
Reminds me of when Betty
and I first fell in love.

27:56.669 --> 27:58.680
I had just finished
my fruit cobbler right and...

28:02.973 --> 28:07.199
You're a very difficult person
to contact, Spider-Man.

28:11.064 --> 28:12.100
You're Nick Fury.

28:13.097 --> 28:14.315
And you just shot Ned.

28:14.738 --> 28:16.956
It's just a mild tranquilizer.
He'll be alright.

28:17.112 --> 28:19.836
So good to finally meet you.

28:20.508 --> 28:21.780
I saw you at the funeral,

28:21.782 --> 28:24.320
but I didn't think that was a good time
to exchange numbers.

28:24.494 --> 28:26.451
No, that would have been
really inappropriate.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.575
That's what I just said.
Right.

28:28.925 --> 28:31.144
The important thing is, you're here.

28:31.384 --> 28:32.673
I tried to bring you here.

28:32.751 --> 28:35.503
You avoided me and now you're here.

28:35.667 --> 28:37.044
What a coincidence.

28:37.416 --> 28:39.654
Wait. Was this a coincidence?

28:40.110 --> 28:42.600
I used to know everything.

28:43.040 --> 28:46.251
Then I come back five years later,
and now I know nothing.

28:46.879 --> 28:49.038
No intel, no team.

28:49.700 --> 28:51.770
And a high school kid

28:51.772 --> 28:54.145
is dodging my calls.

28:55.057 --> 28:56.443
Here's what I do know.

28:58.999 --> 29:00.184
A week ago,

29:00.477 --> 29:02.009
a village in Mexico,

29:02.011 --> 29:04.005
was wiped out by a cyclone.

29:04.959 --> 29:07.785
Witnesses say that cyclone had a face.

29:11.959 --> 29:13.377
Three days later,

29:13.793 --> 29:15.640
a similar event in Morocco.

29:16.369 --> 29:17.485
A village was...

29:19.091 --> 29:20.207
Just making the rounds.

29:20.300 --> 29:23.759
See if anyone needs any emotional
counseling after today's traumatic events.

29:24.018 --> 29:26.383
No, we'll be ok.
We're fine. Thank you.

29:26.473 --> 29:28.530
Great because I'm...
I'm not qualified...

29:29.123 --> 29:30.308
to actually...

29:30.310 --> 29:31.346
he's passed out.

29:31.727 --> 29:34.600
I'm not qualified to do it anyway,
so good night.

29:36.381 --> 29:37.404
That was my teacher.

29:37.406 --> 29:39.693
Sorry about that.
You were saying?

29:39.778 --> 29:43.145
A village was destroyed by what
may well be another world-threatening...

29:43.147 --> 29:46.191
Babe, you still awake?
You're not answering any of my texts.

29:46.897 --> 29:47.992
He's asleep, Betty.

29:48.987 --> 29:49.678
Already?

29:50.054 --> 29:51.409
Yeah.
Ok.

29:51.697 --> 29:53.499
That's why it's imperative...

29:53.617 --> 29:57.711
Hey, boys. So that canal water today
was filled with dangerous bacteria...

29:57.796 --> 30:01.540
Another person touches that door,
you and I are going to attend another funeral.

30:01.633 --> 30:04.671
Suit up.
Let me know if you develop vomiting.

30:08.729 --> 30:10.340
Stark left these for you.

30:10.851 --> 30:11.851
Really?

30:22.904 --> 30:26.443
An uneasy lies the head
that wears the crown.

30:27.783 --> 30:31.279
Stark said you would not get that
because it's not a Star Wars reference.

30:36.363 --> 30:38.705
You can lose the mask.
Everyone here has seen you without it.

30:38.795 --> 30:40.651
You'd be feigning anonymity

30:40.653 --> 30:42.894
and breathing through spandex
for no good reason.

30:48.305 --> 30:49.305
Come on.

30:50.390 --> 30:51.390
Yeah.

30:54.951 --> 30:57.364
Over there, we have Maria Hill.

30:58.458 --> 31:00.916
That is Dimitri.

31:01.976 --> 31:03.216
And this,

31:03.491 --> 31:05.418
is Mr. Beck.

31:07.491 --> 31:08.491
Mysterio?

31:08.950 --> 31:09.857
What?

31:11.036 --> 31:12.016
Doesn't matter.

31:12.018 --> 31:13.871
It's just what my friends
have been calling you.

31:14.033 --> 31:14.983
Well,

31:15.157 --> 31:16.485
you can call me Quentin.

31:19.920 --> 31:21.753
You handled yourself
well out there today.

31:21.755 --> 31:23.255
I saw what you did with the tower.

31:23.340 --> 31:25.252
We could use someone like you
on my world.

31:25.505 --> 31:26.408
Thanks.

31:27.224 --> 31:28.457
I'm sorry. Your world?

31:28.511 --> 31:31.128
Mr. Beck is from Earth.

31:31.431 --> 31:32.967
Just not yours.

31:33.097 --> 31:34.804
There are multiple realities, Peter.

31:35.038 --> 31:38.156
This is Earth Dimension 616.
I'm from Earth 833.

31:38.688 --> 31:41.180
I'm sorry, you're saying
there is a multiverse?

31:41.274 --> 31:42.654
Cuz, I thought that was just theoretical.

31:42.656 --> 31:45.493
I mean, that completely changes
how we understand the initial singularity.

31:45.495 --> 31:47.954
We're talking about
an eternal inflation system.

31:47.956 --> 31:49.948
And, how does that even work
with all the quantum?

31:49.950 --> 31:50.950
It's insane.

31:52.369 --> 31:53.246
Sorry.

31:54.345 --> 31:55.276
It's really cool.

31:56.729 --> 31:58.958
Don't ever apologize for being
the smartest one in the room.

32:01.341 --> 32:02.073
Anyway...

32:05.121 --> 32:08.020
They were born in stable orbits
within black holes.

32:08.059 --> 32:10.135
Creatures formed
from the primary elements:

32:10.137 --> 32:12.675
Air, water, fire, earth.

32:12.988 --> 32:15.367
The Science Division had
a technical name.

32:15.392 --> 32:17.699
We just called them Elementals.

32:17.957 --> 32:19.974
Versions of them exist
across our mythologies.

32:20.063 --> 32:21.850
Turns out, the myths are real.

32:22.184 --> 32:22.941
Like Thor.

32:23.817 --> 32:24.989
Thor was a myth and...

32:24.991 --> 32:26.988
now I study him in my physics class.

32:27.323 --> 32:29.530
These myths are threats.

32:30.007 --> 32:32.249
They first materialized
on my Earth many years ago.

32:32.288 --> 32:33.752
We mobilized and fought them,

32:33.893 --> 32:36.240
but with each battle,
they grew, got stronger.

32:36.554 --> 32:39.349
I was part of the last battalion left
trying to stop them.

32:39.749 --> 32:41.581
All we did was delay the inevitable.

32:41.668 --> 32:43.475
The Elementals are here now,

32:43.477 --> 32:45.133
attacking the same coordinates.

32:45.135 --> 32:46.296
Our satellites confirm it.

32:46.645 --> 32:49.006
Thank Mr. Beck for destroying
the other three.

32:49.092 --> 32:50.221
There's only one left.

32:50.517 --> 32:51.197
Fire.

32:51.512 --> 32:52.937
The strongest of them all.

32:53.536 --> 32:55.098
The one that destroyed my Earth.

32:56.975 --> 32:58.762
It's the one that took my family.

33:02.314 --> 33:03.340
I'm sorry.

33:03.850 --> 33:06.308
And it will be in Prague
in approximately 48 hours.

33:06.544 --> 33:07.670
We have one mission.

33:08.156 --> 33:09.010
Kill it.

33:09.473 --> 33:10.859
And you're coming with us.

33:12.621 --> 33:14.054
I'm sorry, did you say Prague?

33:15.139 --> 33:17.078
Mr. Fury, this all
seems like big-time,

33:17.472 --> 33:19.624
you know, huge
superhero kind of stuff.

33:20.195 --> 33:23.729
And I'm just a friendly
neighborhood Spider-Man, sir.

33:23.791 --> 33:25.623
Bitch, please.
You've been to space.

33:25.679 --> 33:26.898
I know, but that was an accident.

33:26.900 --> 33:27.531
Sir, come on.

33:27.533 --> 33:29.198
There's got to be
someone else you can use.

33:30.213 --> 33:32.132
What about Thor?
Off-world.

33:32.453 --> 33:34.181
Ok, Doctor Strange.

33:34.196 --> 33:35.676
Unavailable.
Captain Marvel.

33:35.770 --> 33:36.922
Don't invoke her name.

33:37.140 --> 33:38.906
Sir look I wanna help. I do.

33:39.294 --> 33:41.929
But if my aunt finds out I left
my class trip, she's gonna kill me.

33:41.976 --> 33:44.382
And if I'm seen like this in Europe
after the Washington Monument,

33:44.402 --> 33:46.750
my class whole class
will figure out who I am, then...

33:47.050 --> 33:49.610
Then the whole world will figure out
who I am, and then I'm done.

33:50.962 --> 33:51.739
Ok.

33:52.155 --> 33:53.278
I understand.

33:55.033 --> 33:56.033
I'm sorry, what?

33:56.117 --> 33:58.825
Why don't you get back
before your teachers miss you

33:58.912 --> 34:00.477
and become suspicious.

34:01.669 --> 34:02.667
Dimitri.

34:02.856 --> 34:05.098
Take him back to the hotel, please.

34:05.293 --> 34:06.204
Yes.

34:06.294 --> 34:07.610
Thank you, Mr. Fury.

34:08.473 --> 34:09.249
And...

34:09.688 --> 34:10.663
good luck.

34:12.332 --> 34:13.456
See you, kid.

34:13.885 --> 34:14.966
Yeah, see you.

34:17.013 --> 34:18.800
Bye, ma'am.
Yeah.

34:24.435 --> 34:27.474
Drink lots of water.
I'm gonna get you a vitamin C pill.

34:27.490 --> 34:30.358
You cannot get sick, ok babe?
Ok. Thanks, baby.

34:30.448 --> 34:32.037
Hey Ned, are you sure you're good?

34:32.357 --> 34:34.086
Dude, I'm fine.

34:34.088 --> 34:35.293
Ok. Nice.
Don't worry.

34:35.448 --> 34:38.282
Seriously, getting tranq'd
in the neck by Nick Fury,

34:38.546 --> 34:40.221
probably the coolest thing
to ever happen to me anyway.

34:40.245 --> 34:41.534
It is pretty awesome.
Yeah.

34:41.714 --> 34:43.405
I'm just happy
I don't have to go to Prague.

34:43.494 --> 34:44.527
Seriously.
Good news.

34:45.029 --> 34:46.143
We're going to Prague.

34:47.502 --> 34:48.868
What?
Prague?

34:48.875 --> 34:49.533
Yeah.

34:49.935 --> 34:51.770
Tour company called.
They upgraded us.

34:52.048 --> 34:53.369
You should have heard
me on the phone with them.

34:53.607 --> 34:55.008
I really gave them hell.

34:55.093 --> 34:56.093
All I heard was crying.

34:56.775 --> 34:59.225
Look at our upgraded ride.
Bro, you see that?

34:59.264 --> 35:00.236
It's pretty sick.

35:00.515 --> 35:02.126
I'm impressed, Mr. Harrington.

35:02.304 --> 35:03.385
Come on.

35:04.144 --> 35:05.045
Peter, what?

35:05.601 --> 35:06.605
What's going on?

35:07.874 --> 35:10.648
I think Nick Fury just hijacked
our summer vacation.

35:11.429 --> 35:14.139
I'm Mr. Harrington to the kids...

35:14.771 --> 35:16.396
alright.
Ok.

35:16.670 --> 35:17.607
Awesome.

35:18.658 --> 35:20.445
Yeah. Awesome.

35:43.642 --> 35:46.384
Yo, what's up, Flash Mob?
It's your boy, the Big F,

35:46.438 --> 35:49.071
cruising through the Alps
with my private driver, Dimitri.

36:10.533 --> 36:12.805
For the next Tony Stark, I trust you.

36:13.213 --> 36:14.920
Say EDITH.

36:16.941 --> 36:19.386
<i>Stand by for retinal
and biometric scan.</i>

36:20.136 --> 36:23.004
<i>Retinal and biometric scan accepted.</i>
Hello?

36:23.152 --> 36:24.406
<i>Hello, Peter.</i>

36:24.641 --> 36:25.735
<i>I am EDITH,</i>

36:25.892 --> 36:29.341
<i>Tony Stark's augmented-reality
security and defense system.</i>

36:29.813 --> 36:31.520
So he made you for me?
<i>No.</i>

36:31.653 --> 36:34.066
<i>But you have access
to all of Tony's protocols.</i>

36:34.109 --> 36:34.941
Cool.

36:35.098 --> 36:36.900
<i>Would you like to see what I can do?</i>

36:42.242 --> 36:46.202
<i>EDITH stands for Even dead,
I'm the hero.</i>

36:46.287 --> 36:48.244
<i>Tony loved his acronyms.</i>

36:48.331 --> 36:49.447
Yeah, he did.

36:49.541 --> 36:52.625
<i>I have access to the entire
Stark Global Security network,</i>

36:52.711 --> 36:54.748
<i>including multiple defense satellites,</i>

36:54.838 --> 36:58.206
<i>as well as back doors
to all major telecommunication networks.</i>

37:05.140 --> 37:06.426
Is MJ texting?

37:09.539 --> 37:11.980
No. Don't look at it. Don't look at it.
Hat's. That's wrong.

37:12.208 --> 37:13.326
That's wrong.

37:30.869 --> 37:32.857
Petrol and toilets. Ten minutes!

37:33.501 --> 37:35.413
Flash Mob, this is what
we doing out here...

37:35.415 --> 37:37.299
Toilet, toilet, toilet.
Which way to the toilet?

37:37.714 --> 37:38.884
Ten minutes, everyone.

37:39.483 --> 37:42.438
Dimitri, where exactly are we?

37:44.763 --> 37:46.803
Ok. I'll figure it out.
My gosh, it's so sick.

37:46.881 --> 37:48.331
Yeah.
It's beautiful.

37:49.434 --> 37:50.184
What?

38:03.490 --> 38:04.304
Hello.

38:04.908 --> 38:05.682
Close the door.

38:12.066 --> 38:13.073
I'm Peter Parker.

38:13.291 --> 38:14.275
Take off your clothes.

38:16.805 --> 38:17.664
Excuse me?

38:17.666 --> 38:19.761
You told Fury Spider-Man
cannot be seen in Europe.

38:20.527 --> 38:22.253
So I made you this, another suit.

38:24.807 --> 38:25.510
Thank you.

38:26.818 --> 38:29.495
I'm sure it fits fine. I don't need to try...
Take off your clothes.

38:29.972 --> 38:30.691
Ok.

38:32.811 --> 38:33.596
Sure.

38:35.814 --> 38:37.771
It's a little embarrassing.
Now. Hurry up.

38:37.857 --> 38:40.190
This is weird.

38:43.216 --> 38:44.819
No, no, no! Don't go!

38:48.303 --> 38:49.421
Sorry...

38:49.756 --> 38:51.828
I thought this was the bathroom.
This is not what it looks like.

38:51.830 --> 38:52.605
Just...
Yeah.

38:53.131 --> 38:54.997
What are you doing?
I'll leave you two alone.

38:54.999 --> 38:56.774
Oh my God. Don't shoot anybody.

38:56.776 --> 38:58.789
Brad? It's not what it looks like, buddy.

38:59.462 --> 39:00.563
Hey man, look.
Look.

39:00.565 --> 39:01.461
That's...
Peter,

39:01.492 --> 39:03.499
I'm not here to judge
your life choices, dude.

39:03.561 --> 39:06.898
If you want to hook up with some random
European chick on our school trip that's on you.

39:06.900 --> 39:07.990
That's not what that was, honestly.

39:07.992 --> 39:09.971
I can't pretend
I didn't see what I just saw.

39:10.088 --> 39:12.139
I know you're trying to get with MJ.
It's obvious.

39:12.416 --> 39:13.334
But I like her too.

39:13.336 --> 39:14.442
Wait a minute. Hey, hey.

39:14.456 --> 39:16.196
You cannot show her
that photo, dude, come on.

39:16.346 --> 39:17.848
I'm sorry man. I have to.

39:18.173 --> 39:19.539
She deserves the truth.

39:21.043 --> 39:23.239
Ok, put your one foot
in front of the other,

39:23.241 --> 39:25.153
and everybody back on the bus.

39:25.155 --> 39:26.754
It's been 10 minutes. Let's go!

39:31.828 --> 39:33.593
What's up, Flash Mob?
It's your boy, Big F...

39:34.330 --> 39:35.076
EDITH?

39:35.256 --> 39:37.078
<i>Hello, Peter. How can I help you?</i>

39:37.124 --> 39:37.707
Hey...

39:38.468 --> 39:40.027
There's this guy in my class who's
kinda gonna ruin everything

39:40.029 --> 39:40.655
with MJ...
<i>Peter,</i>

39:40.657 --> 39:41.754
<i>I'm having difficulty hearing you.</i>

39:41.935 --> 39:43.365
<i>Can you please speak up?</i>

39:44.467 --> 39:46.448
Brad Davis. He has a photo of me?

39:46.534 --> 39:48.320
<i>Brad Davis. Is he a target?</i>

39:48.511 --> 39:49.671
Is Brad a target?

39:55.592 --> 39:57.513
Yeah. He's a target. He's a target.

39:57.515 --> 39:58.407
<i>Copy that.</i>

39:58.688 --> 40:01.588
<i>Target is Brad Davis.
Initiating strike.</i>

40:01.858 --> 40:03.049
Initiating what, now?

40:03.051 --> 40:04.218
<i>Intercept point determined.</i>

40:04.383 --> 40:05.636
<i>Releasing kill vehicle.</i>

40:05.638 --> 40:06.287
EDITH.

40:29.719 --> 40:30.692
Oh my God.

40:30.694 --> 40:31.886
Dope glasses, Parker.

40:31.888 --> 40:33.614
How'd you pay for these?
Flash, give them back.

40:33.615 --> 40:34.308
No, no, no, no.
Flash!

40:34.309 --> 40:35.679
I'm really paying you a compliment.
Please give me...

40:37.726 --> 40:38.726
I'm so sorry.

40:40.855 --> 40:42.201
EDITH, don't kill Brad.

40:42.203 --> 40:44.713
<i>Peter, do you want me to cancel
the drone strike on Brad Davis?</i>

40:44.715 --> 40:45.841
Did you punch Flash?

40:45.865 --> 40:47.061
No.
<i>Firing.</i>

40:50.475 --> 40:51.053
Look out!

40:55.640 --> 40:57.427
Hey, this is not the autobahn!

40:57.713 --> 40:58.428
EDITH.

40:58.915 --> 41:00.513
Is this the autobahn?
Appears to be.

41:02.710 --> 41:04.451
<i>Commencing second strike.</i>
Peter.

41:04.545 --> 41:06.749
Plant your fanny in that seat
and buckle up right now.

41:06.751 --> 41:07.740
Look at the baby mountain goats!

41:07.842 --> 41:10.004
Baby mountain goats?
I see them.

41:24.107 --> 41:26.076
I don't see any mountain goats.

41:26.613 --> 41:27.791
You missed them.

41:28.209 --> 41:30.357
I know you think none of us
have noticed, Peter...

41:30.618 --> 41:31.446
What?

41:31.864 --> 41:33.042
But your new look,

41:33.612 --> 41:34.546
I love it.

41:35.118 --> 41:36.359
Right, babe?
Thanks.

41:36.361 --> 41:39.056
Yeah. Sophisticated, classy,
very European.

41:39.455 --> 41:40.455
Man.

41:41.958 --> 41:43.324
Let's try that again.

41:44.870 --> 41:47.039
This is so weird.
It was right here on my phone.

41:47.041 --> 41:48.042
I... I...
Yeah.

41:48.981 --> 41:49.844
Weird.

42:19.203 --> 42:21.215
Freaking beautiful.
This is amazing.

42:23.005 --> 42:24.715
This place is so classy.

42:24.717 --> 42:26.098
Yeah, so why are we here?

42:26.350 --> 42:27.537
Speak for yourself.

42:27.683 --> 42:28.887
I'm home.

42:29.630 --> 42:30.570
What can I say?

42:31.487 --> 42:33.541
The squeaky wheel gets
the upgrade grease.

42:33.751 --> 42:37.455
Everyone get settled in, rest up
because tonight, big surprise,

42:37.501 --> 42:40.930
is Prague's annual Carnival of Lights.

42:41.161 --> 42:42.258
Yeah!
Hello?

42:42.503 --> 42:44.764
<i>Parker, it's Hill.
There's an earpiece with your suit.</i>

42:44.854 --> 42:47.106
<i>Put it on and await further instructions.
Understood?</i>

42:47.335 --> 42:48.779
Yes, ma'am.
<i>Yeah.</i>

42:49.176 --> 42:50.021
Hey, man.
Hey.

42:50.065 --> 42:51.777
Look, I am so sorry,

42:52.028 --> 42:54.757
if I seem like I'm preoccupied
with my relationship.

42:54.830 --> 42:56.193
You know I'm still your guy in the chair.

42:56.195 --> 42:57.948
No, no, no. It's all good.
Don't worry about it.

42:58.020 --> 43:00.216
Ok. Great, great.
It's fine.

43:00.745 --> 43:03.078
So, what's the status
on the Elemental thing?

43:03.337 --> 43:04.729
Where's it gonna happen?

43:05.001 --> 43:05.931
Here in the city.

43:06.025 --> 43:08.120
Peter we're here.
I know. I know, it's not good.

43:08.211 --> 43:09.418
I'm figuring it out.

43:10.094 --> 43:11.647
You have to do
something Peter, please.

43:11.649 --> 43:12.954
We're counting on you.

43:13.183 --> 43:14.765
Ned.
Yeah. Yeah, babe.

43:15.022 --> 43:16.983
The good news is,
we've all got our own rooms.

43:17.470 --> 43:19.257
It's about time.
Serious?

43:19.347 --> 43:20.129
<i>Parker?</i>

43:20.746 --> 43:21.968
Parker!
Yes, sir.

43:22.159 --> 43:24.446
That thing is going to be here
in a few hours.

43:24.623 --> 43:25.801
Are we boring you?

43:26.094 --> 43:28.651
He's not bored. He's thinking
about how you kidnapped him.

43:28.807 --> 43:29.679
He had obstacles.

43:30.108 --> 43:31.974
I removed them.

43:32.068 --> 43:33.900
They still won't evacuate the city.

43:35.113 --> 43:36.113
Idiots.

43:37.054 --> 43:38.590
So, what's the plan, Parker?

43:38.991 --> 43:41.013
I will be in the cathedral tower,

43:41.398 --> 43:42.559
keeping watch for the fire monster.

43:42.561 --> 43:44.915
When that shows up,
I will radio you guys,

43:45.331 --> 43:48.074
and then Mr. Beck and I will...
My name is Mysterio.

43:51.926 --> 43:53.959
That's when Mysterio
and I will move in.

43:54.375 --> 43:55.380
Peter, listen to me.

43:55.718 --> 43:57.859
The best hope you have,
the only hope,

43:58.233 --> 43:59.640
is to stop it here now,

43:59.832 --> 44:01.083
no matter what the cost.

44:01.854 --> 44:03.714
Maneuver it away
from civilians if you can,

44:03.808 --> 44:06.676
but most important,
keep it away from metal.

44:07.095 --> 44:08.154
If it gets too big,

44:08.156 --> 44:10.309
it'll be able to draw power
from the Earth's core.

44:10.546 --> 44:11.398
After that,

44:11.600 --> 44:13.267
there is no way to stop it.

44:17.809 --> 44:19.238
Hey, my friends are here.

44:19.687 --> 44:21.610
I can't help but think
we're putting them in danger.

44:21.701 --> 44:24.628
You're worried about us
hurting your friends?

44:24.871 --> 44:29.206
You, who called a drone strike
on your own school tour bus?

44:30.001 --> 44:35.668
Stark gave you a multi-billion dollar
A.R. tactical intelligence system,

44:35.966 --> 44:38.669
and the first thing you do with it is try
and blow up your friends.

44:38.966 --> 44:43.528
It's clear to me
that you were not ready for this.

44:50.965 --> 44:53.320
Fury asked me to come up here
and see how you were doing.

44:53.322 --> 44:55.406
He just...
He felt bad about snapping at you.

44:55.614 --> 44:56.417
Really?

44:56.768 --> 44:59.260
You guys do have sarcasm
on this Earth, right?

45:00.825 --> 45:02.111
How you feeling?

45:06.704 --> 45:09.568
I didn't think I was gonna have
to save the world this summer.

45:10.416 --> 45:12.641
I know that makes me sound
like such a jerk. I just...

45:14.295 --> 45:16.915
I had this plan with this girl
that I really like...

45:17.924 --> 45:20.132
and now it's all ruined.

45:27.558 --> 45:29.971
You're not a jerk
for wanting a normal life, kid.

45:32.244 --> 45:33.308
It's a hard path.

45:34.273 --> 45:35.979
You see things. You do things.

45:36.121 --> 45:37.368
You make choices.

45:38.704 --> 45:40.050
People look up to you...

45:41.906 --> 45:44.047
and even if you win a battle,
sometimes they die.

45:45.486 --> 45:47.530
I like you, Peter. You're a good kid.

45:48.913 --> 45:51.902
There's a part of me
that wants me to tell you, just...

45:52.913 --> 45:54.745
turn around, run away from all this.

45:54.791 --> 45:56.244
Then there is another part of me that...

45:56.640 --> 45:58.081
knows what we're about to fight,

45:58.756 --> 45:59.957
what's at stake,

46:00.365 --> 46:01.525
and I'm glad you're here.

46:03.427 --> 46:04.427
Me too.

46:04.512 --> 46:05.127
But...

46:05.348 --> 46:06.555
you're worried about your friends.

46:06.990 --> 46:07.666
Yeah.

46:09.180 --> 46:11.155
Just always feel like
I'm putting them in danger.

46:11.686 --> 46:12.660
Look just...

46:13.663 --> 46:17.129
get them inside and keep them
in a safe place for just a few hours.

46:17.131 --> 46:18.131
They'll be alright.

46:19.763 --> 46:20.794
It's really nice...

46:21.278 --> 46:22.690
to have somebody to talk to about,

46:22.933 --> 46:24.267
superhero stuff, you know?

46:26.062 --> 46:26.963
Anytime.

46:27.636 --> 46:28.467
And hey,

46:29.055 --> 46:31.755
we survive this,
you'll have all summer to kill Brad.

46:35.626 --> 46:36.604
See you out there.

46:37.425 --> 46:38.137
Alright.

46:42.850 --> 46:44.841
Mi scusi. Sorry, that's Italian.

46:48.303 --> 46:49.042
Ok.

46:49.542 --> 46:51.424
EDITH?
Come on.

46:51.672 --> 46:52.970
<i>Hello, Peter.</i>
Hey.

46:53.568 --> 46:56.183
I need to find a way to keep my friends
inside for the next few hours.

46:56.231 --> 46:57.591
<i>Let's see what we can do.</i>

46:58.007 --> 46:59.068
Good news.

46:59.992 --> 47:01.135
We're going to the opera!

47:01.621 --> 47:02.942
You're kidding me.
The opera?

47:03.463 --> 47:05.697
Don't look at me.
What happened to the carnival?

47:05.830 --> 47:07.155
This is upgrade living, guys.

47:07.469 --> 47:10.983
Come on. The tour company
just gave us these tickets.

47:11.144 --> 47:12.166
For free!

47:12.568 --> 47:14.369
Do you have any idea how
much opera tickets cost?

47:14.383 --> 47:17.847
No, because none of us have
ever wanted to go to the opera,

47:17.849 --> 47:18.754
ever.

47:19.374 --> 47:21.711
Well, I think this is gonna be
culturally enriching for us.

47:21.890 --> 47:22.847
Thank you, Ned.

47:23.382 --> 47:24.273
Everyone,

47:24.874 --> 47:26.376
this is gonna be, maybe,

47:26.628 --> 47:29.433
the best four hours of our whole trip.

47:29.511 --> 47:30.758
Four hours?

47:30.848 --> 47:33.340
Guys, I think this is gonna be
really fun. Seriously.

47:35.892 --> 47:39.012
I bet now you're all happy
I had you pack a nice outfit.

47:39.106 --> 47:41.646
Yeah, because we'd much rather go
to a four-hour opera

47:41.648 --> 47:43.618
instead of the biggest party in the world.

47:43.659 --> 47:45.446
Again, don't look at me.

47:46.590 --> 47:47.825
<i>Parker, do you copy?</i>

47:48.115 --> 47:49.481
<i>Comm check, one, two.</i>

47:51.973 --> 47:53.570
Ok, here we are.

47:54.615 --> 47:55.433
Beat the rush.

47:55.767 --> 47:56.992
Yeah, the rush out.

47:57.375 --> 47:58.440
Lucky for us,

47:58.442 --> 48:00.369
we got the best seats in the house.

48:01.462 --> 48:02.498
Let's go.

48:04.131 --> 48:05.963
Hey. I'll save you a seat.

48:13.538 --> 48:15.060
You look really pretty.

48:15.062 --> 48:16.510
And therefore, I have value?

48:17.176 --> 48:19.709
No, that's not what I meant at all.
I was just...

48:19.711 --> 48:20.746
I'm messing with you.

48:22.149 --> 48:23.127
Thank you.

48:23.638 --> 48:24.357
You're welcome.

48:24.359 --> 48:25.690
You look pretty too.

48:26.535 --> 48:27.202
Thank you.

48:27.204 --> 48:29.696
Oh my gosh! Opera glasses!
So cute.

48:29.698 --> 48:31.128
Can I?
Yeah.

48:31.627 --> 48:33.334
Want to go in on a pair?

48:34.078 --> 48:35.687
You mean us sit next to each other?

48:35.798 --> 48:36.548
Yeah.

48:36.747 --> 48:38.070
<i>Are you in position?</i>

48:38.582 --> 48:39.317
No.

48:39.411 --> 48:40.541
Ok. No...

48:40.767 --> 48:43.126
<i>Why the hell not? Parker?</i>
You don't want to sit next to me,

48:43.128 --> 48:45.060
or no you just don't want the glasses?

48:45.139 --> 48:46.390
I didn't mean that.

48:46.966 --> 48:49.485
If you go ahead, I'll go grab us a pair.

48:50.894 --> 48:52.677
I'll save you a seat next to me.

48:52.837 --> 48:55.096
A lot of seats, so I'll be up there.

48:56.250 --> 48:56.820
Ok.

48:57.059 --> 48:57.890
<i>Parker?</i>

48:58.188 --> 48:59.391
No, I'm coming. I'm...

49:00.271 --> 49:01.422
Hey, I got to go.

49:01.784 --> 49:04.200
Could you tell MJ that
I'm sick or something?

49:04.378 --> 49:06.244
Ok. Be careful.

49:06.429 --> 49:07.484
And whatever you do,

49:07.499 --> 49:10.347
please steer the monster away
from the opera house.

49:10.948 --> 49:12.109
Yeah, Ned, I know.

49:12.346 --> 49:13.199
Ok.
Ok?

49:13.242 --> 49:14.858
Yeah.
Gotta go.

49:29.884 --> 49:30.947
<i>Parker!</i>

49:30.949 --> 49:32.550
<i>You better be on your way.</i>

49:32.928 --> 49:33.964
Coming.

49:40.354 --> 49:42.795
Where do you think she's going?
Do you think she's going to the carnival?

49:42.797 --> 49:44.987
I... I don't...
We should go. Yes, we should go.

49:45.044 --> 49:47.502
Come on, let's go. Come on.

50:03.334 --> 50:05.204
Alright. I'm in position.

50:06.032 --> 50:07.778
As soon as I see something, Beck, I'll...

50:08.229 --> 50:09.335
I'll let you know.

50:09.423 --> 50:11.506
<i>Roger that.
How's the suit?</i>

50:11.592 --> 50:12.662
The suit's great.

50:12.927 --> 50:13.947
It's awesome.

50:14.263 --> 50:16.263
It's a little tight around
the old web-shooter.

50:16.265 --> 50:18.222
<i>Parker!</i>
Ok, I'll shut up.

50:18.247 --> 50:20.739
My God, babe, isn't this beautiful?

50:20.741 --> 50:23.074
Yeah, it's real beautiful, babe.

50:23.229 --> 50:24.138
What's wrong?

50:25.290 --> 50:26.473
You know honestly, I just...

50:26.565 --> 50:29.103
I don't do well with big crowds,
so maybe we should...

50:29.193 --> 50:31.981
I have the perfect thing.
Come on.

50:40.788 --> 50:42.120
Don't worry, babe.

50:42.206 --> 50:44.539
We'll get away from the crowds,
get some fresh air.

50:44.867 --> 50:46.665
You'll feel a thousand times better.

50:51.757 --> 50:53.919
Energy spiking.
We have seismic activity.

51:05.881 --> 51:07.800
Ok, he's here! Beck, you ready?

51:07.815 --> 51:08.844
You know what to do.

51:09.190 --> 51:10.220
On your lead, Spider-Man.

51:16.323 --> 51:17.323
No, come back!

51:17.408 --> 51:19.067
Come back and help us!

51:25.754 --> 51:26.995
You're up, kid.

51:39.933 --> 51:40.891
Wait, wait, wait. Is that?

51:41.616 --> 51:42.887
Do you think that's Spider-Man?

51:43.809 --> 51:46.333
No, no, no.
It's like a European rip-off version of him.

51:46.335 --> 51:48.113
I was actually reading about him
the other day. It's not him.

52:01.601 --> 52:03.593
No, Beck! He's got the carousel!

52:03.774 --> 52:04.981
He's getting bigger!

52:05.414 --> 52:07.155
What's his... What's his name?
What's his name?

52:08.045 --> 52:09.078
Night... Night Monkey.

52:09.168 --> 52:10.328
Night Monkey?
Yeah.

52:10.468 --> 52:11.955
Yeah.
Night Monkey!

52:12.046 --> 52:13.120
Yeah.
Night Monkey!

52:13.231 --> 52:14.311
Help!
Night Monkey!

52:14.313 --> 52:15.047
Save us! What?

52:15.049 --> 52:16.468
Night Monkey, we're stuck!

52:16.519 --> 52:18.260
No, no.
Help us! Help!

52:33.408 --> 52:34.150
Are you ok?

52:38.554 --> 52:39.404
On to Plan B?

52:39.406 --> 52:40.254
Yeah!

52:40.340 --> 52:41.929
We got to hit him
with something he can't absorb!

52:42.049 --> 52:44.408
I go left, you go right! Now!

53:00.674 --> 53:01.881
Ok, shoot him!

53:02.054 --> 53:03.054
Yeah!

53:05.641 --> 53:07.428
That hurt him. Keep it coming.

53:15.651 --> 53:17.608
<i>Spider-Man, keep your distance.</i>

53:17.695 --> 53:18.850
<i>I'm trying!</i>

53:19.613 --> 53:21.525
<i>Can't let him get near
the Ferris wheel.</i>

53:21.615 --> 53:23.151
<i>Ok. I'm on it!</i>

53:46.265 --> 53:47.631
What is that?!

53:55.441 --> 53:56.898
Betty! Betty!

54:17.546 --> 54:20.505
That's it! Nice! Nice! You got him!

54:26.930 --> 54:28.399
No, no, no.

54:35.444 --> 54:36.425
It's too late.

54:37.987 --> 54:38.954
Whatever happens...

54:39.777 --> 54:41.090
I'm glad we met.

54:41.487 --> 54:43.319
Beck, what are you doing?

54:44.573 --> 54:46.608
What I should have done last time.

54:51.830 --> 54:52.946
Beck, don't do it!

54:57.586 --> 54:58.702
Beck!

55:19.024 --> 55:20.024
Mr. Beck?

55:23.278 --> 55:24.394
Thank God.

55:33.413 --> 55:36.798
I would totally kiss you, but I think
I just threw up in my mouth a little.

55:40.796 --> 55:42.130
I might have a mint.

55:44.260 --> 55:45.296
So it's over?

55:45.414 --> 55:46.747
That was the last of them.

55:47.010 --> 55:49.355
But not the last threat we'll ever face.

55:50.392 --> 55:53.439
We need to stay vigilant.

55:54.099 --> 55:56.488
There's a void in this world
for someone like you.

55:56.793 --> 55:59.952
Hill and I are going to Europol
headquarters in Berlin tomorrow.

56:00.399 --> 56:01.640
You should join us.

56:03.652 --> 56:04.568
Thank you.

56:04.995 --> 56:06.541
I just might take you up on that.

56:16.832 --> 56:18.667
You got gifts, Parker,

56:19.201 --> 56:20.508
but you didn't wanna be here.

56:20.510 --> 56:23.286
Mr. Fury, I...
I'd love to have you in Berlin too.

56:24.817 --> 56:28.129
But you got to decide whether
you're going to step up or not.

56:29.261 --> 56:30.420
Stark chose you.

56:30.959 --> 56:32.857
He made you an Avenger.

56:33.682 --> 56:34.628
I need that.

56:35.684 --> 56:37.971
The world needs that.

56:38.672 --> 56:39.531
Maybe Stark was wrong.

56:43.650 --> 56:44.755
Was he?

56:46.945 --> 56:48.198
The choice is yours.

57:03.295 --> 57:04.502
Let's get a drink.

57:07.883 --> 57:09.157
I'm not 21.

57:16.475 --> 57:17.475
Hey.

57:20.187 --> 57:21.390
You got to celebrate.

57:21.478 --> 57:22.833
We did something good tonight.

57:22.981 --> 57:23.781
Yeah.

57:25.317 --> 57:26.367
Fury was right.

57:27.410 --> 57:28.793
Tony did a lot for me so...

57:29.821 --> 57:31.813
I owe it to him, to everybody.

57:32.658 --> 57:33.576
Do you?

57:34.194 --> 57:35.708
Yeah. I mean...

57:37.663 --> 57:38.690
Mr. Stark...

57:39.381 --> 57:40.499
gave me the chance to be more.

57:40.500 --> 57:42.332
He wanted me to be better than him.

57:42.453 --> 57:45.327
And Fury just wants me to live up to that.
What do you want, Peter?

57:45.879 --> 57:47.693
What do you mean?
What do you want?

57:50.159 --> 57:51.160
I don't know.

57:51.227 --> 57:52.808
What do you want, you?
Peter Parker. Now.

57:52.810 --> 57:54.811
I know you're thinking about it.
I wanna go on my trip.

57:55.077 --> 57:55.744
Alright.

57:55.746 --> 57:57.595
I want to go back on my trip
with my friends.

57:58.179 --> 58:00.709
And go to the top of the Eiffel Tower

58:01.259 --> 58:04.312
with the girl who I really like
and tell her how I feel and...

58:06.388 --> 58:07.754
give her a kiss.

58:08.402 --> 58:09.705
Shut up, man.

58:10.404 --> 58:11.908
You're not gonna do that, are you?

58:11.910 --> 58:13.487
No, I can't.
Why not?

58:13.627 --> 58:15.778
Because I have too much
of a responsibility.

58:18.148 --> 58:20.053
Oh my God. Thank you so much.
What are those?

58:20.330 --> 58:22.149
Are those the?
EDITH glasses, yeah.

58:22.204 --> 58:23.286
They were just on the floor?

58:24.350 --> 58:25.667
Try them on.
Let's see how they look on you.

58:25.762 --> 58:26.762
Yeah?
Yeah.

58:30.626 --> 58:31.892
I actually really like them.

58:32.531 --> 58:33.978
Can I be completely honest with you?

58:34.142 --> 58:34.759
Please.

58:35.324 --> 58:36.476
They look really stupid.

58:38.726 --> 58:40.558
But maybe they have
a contact-lens version.

58:40.920 --> 58:41.887
You try them on.

58:42.203 --> 58:43.910
No, come on.
Try them on.

58:44.199 --> 58:46.074
I don't wanna try them on.
Just put them on.

58:53.780 --> 58:54.945
What do you think, kid?

59:00.078 --> 59:01.806
Next Tony Stark, I trust you.

59:03.480 --> 59:05.504
For the next Tony Stark, I trust you.

59:05.880 --> 59:06.653
What?

59:07.294 --> 59:09.081
Mr. Stark left me a message
with those glasses:

59:09.171 --> 59:11.003
For the next Tony Stark, I trust you.

59:11.368 --> 59:13.672
I'm still not following.
How many lemonades have you had?

59:13.925 --> 59:15.625
He knew every mistake I ever made.

59:15.696 --> 59:18.256
Ok he must've known I wasn't ready
for something like this.

59:18.721 --> 59:19.721
Why give it to you?

59:19.821 --> 59:23.377
Because maybe he didn't trust me to have EDITH,
he just trusted me to pick who should.

59:23.769 --> 59:26.256
It makes so much more sense.
He always knew I'd do what's right.

59:26.258 --> 59:28.014
And he's not gonna give them
to Fury because...

59:28.016 --> 59:29.753
Fury would give himself EDITH.

59:29.878 --> 59:31.174
You're probably right about that.

59:31.240 --> 59:33.932
Right, so the world needs
the next Iron Man.

59:34.446 --> 59:37.593
And it's not gonna be me.
I'm a 16-year-old kid from Queens.

59:37.595 --> 59:40.312
It needs to be an adult
with some experience

59:40.410 --> 59:42.640
and that's good like Tony Stark, like you.

59:43.455 --> 59:44.932
No. Peter, come on.

59:46.011 --> 59:46.795
No.

59:49.067 --> 59:50.308
EDITH?
<i>Hello, Peter.</i>

59:50.432 --> 59:51.525
Hi. Yeah...

59:53.107 --> 59:56.020
I'd like to transfer your control
over to Quentin Beck.

59:56.309 --> 59:57.338
Peter, what are you doing?

59:57.552 --> 59:58.609
Doing the right thing.

59:58.804 --> 01:00:01.252
<i>Any transfer will require confirmation.</i>

01:00:01.254 --> 01:00:03.127
Stark gave you the glasses.

01:00:03.135 --> 01:00:05.650
Stark gave me a choice.
It's my choice to make, ok?

01:00:05.652 --> 01:00:06.384
And I'm gonna make it.

01:00:06.386 --> 01:00:08.882
Look you're a soldier, a leader.
You stopped the Elementals.

01:00:08.884 --> 01:00:10.913
You saved my life.
You saved the world.

01:00:11.198 --> 01:00:11.878
Ok?

01:00:12.116 --> 01:00:13.516
He'd want you to have them.

01:00:13.736 --> 01:00:15.146
<i>Waiting for confirmation.</i>

01:00:15.338 --> 01:00:16.206
Confirm.

01:00:20.356 --> 01:00:21.767
Welcome to the Avengers.

01:00:30.043 --> 01:00:31.159
They look good on you.

01:00:32.936 --> 01:00:33.936
Thank you.

01:00:34.506 --> 01:00:35.506
It's an honor.

01:00:35.966 --> 01:00:36.966
Yeah.

01:00:38.661 --> 01:00:40.433
Mr. Stark would have really liked you.

01:00:41.930 --> 01:00:42.930
Where you headed?

01:00:43.410 --> 01:00:44.588
I'm gonna go find MJ.

01:00:44.842 --> 01:00:45.723
Good luck, kid.

01:00:45.990 --> 01:00:48.367
I'll give you about a fifty-fifty chance.
You're pretty awkward, so...

01:00:49.646 --> 01:00:50.356
Yeah.

01:00:51.231 --> 01:00:52.120
See you later, man.

01:00:52.364 --> 01:00:53.215
See you.

01:01:25.348 --> 01:01:27.055
See? That wasn't so hard.

01:01:27.142 --> 01:01:28.142
Yes!

01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:32.145
Somebody get this stupid
costume off me!

01:01:39.668 --> 01:01:40.668
<i>Ok, we got EDITH.</i>

01:01:40.889 --> 01:01:42.409
Get these connected to our system.

01:01:42.411 --> 01:01:44.951
Toast! Toast! Toast!

01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:47.701
No, this is a big win,
but we still got a lot of work to do.

01:01:47.787 --> 01:01:49.528
Toast! Toast! Toast!

01:01:49.623 --> 01:01:51.330
Yeah!

01:01:51.455 --> 01:01:53.154
Ok, toasts!

01:01:54.048 --> 01:01:55.086
Give me that, Doug.

01:01:55.900 --> 01:01:59.073
To the man who brought us all together,
our former boss, Tony Stark.

01:02:00.857 --> 01:02:02.083
The jester king.

01:02:02.475 --> 01:02:06.545
Literally wrapped
in wealth and technology

01:02:07.063 --> 01:02:08.869
that he was unfit to wield.

01:02:09.377 --> 01:02:11.133
Like the holographic system I designed.

01:02:11.228 --> 01:02:14.064
A revolutionary breakthrough
with limitless applications

01:02:14.142 --> 01:02:16.425
that Tony turned
into a self-therapy machine

01:02:16.545 --> 01:02:17.334
and renamed...

01:02:17.524 --> 01:02:20.938
Binarily Augmented Retro-Framing,
or BARF.

01:02:24.484 --> 01:02:28.085
$611 million
for my little therapeutic experiment.

01:02:29.746 --> 01:02:32.484
He renamed my life's work BARF.

01:02:32.936 --> 01:02:34.143
I told him it was a mistake,

01:02:34.315 --> 01:02:36.261
that my technology could change
the world.

01:02:37.921 --> 01:02:38.921
And then...

01:02:40.297 --> 01:02:41.292
he fired me.

01:02:42.758 --> 01:02:43.993
Said I was...

01:02:45.512 --> 01:02:46.628
unstable.

01:02:48.598 --> 01:02:49.426
To Tony.

01:02:49.576 --> 01:02:51.205
To Tony!

01:02:51.935 --> 01:02:54.723
Next, to William.
William!

01:02:55.051 --> 01:02:58.557
Tony Stark was able
to build this in a cave!

01:02:58.984 --> 01:03:00.685
With a box of scraps!

01:03:01.553 --> 01:03:04.650
The integration of my illusion tech
with your weaponized drones,

01:03:04.727 --> 01:03:05.614
was brilliant.

01:03:05.786 --> 01:03:08.326
Powerful illusions, real damage,
worked like a charm.

01:03:08.459 --> 01:03:09.532
And it's just the beginning.

01:03:09.664 --> 01:03:10.461
Thank you, brother.

01:03:10.682 --> 01:03:11.629
To Guterman.

01:03:11.665 --> 01:03:12.934
Guterman!
To Guterman!

01:03:12.981 --> 01:03:14.108
The story you created,

01:03:14.110 --> 01:03:16.012
of a soldier from another
Earth named Quentin,

01:03:16.014 --> 01:03:19.081
fighting space monsters
in Europe is totally ridiculous

01:03:19.376 --> 01:03:22.023
and apparently exactly the kind of thing
people will believe right now.

01:03:22.059 --> 01:03:23.672
I mean, everybody bought it.

01:03:23.758 --> 01:03:25.414
Gutes!
Guterman!

01:03:25.562 --> 01:03:27.506
To Victoria.
To Victoria!

01:03:27.600 --> 01:03:29.855
Staging electromagnetic pulses
at each attack site

01:03:29.857 --> 01:03:32.195
so Fury's own satellites
would confirm our lies.

01:03:32.197 --> 01:03:33.567
Inspired idea.

01:03:33.809 --> 01:03:35.963
To Janice.
Janice!

01:03:36.111 --> 01:03:38.164
After Tony died, she was the one
who discovered,

01:03:38.166 --> 01:03:40.195
that EDITH was being
handed over not to us,

01:03:40.278 --> 01:03:42.228
not to the Defense Department,

01:03:42.444 --> 01:03:43.444
but to a child.

01:03:43.486 --> 01:03:45.220
Thank you.
To Janice!

01:03:45.471 --> 01:03:47.534
And to the rest of you,
Tony Stark is gone.

01:03:48.203 --> 01:03:50.987
There is a window of opportunity,
and someone will step up.

01:03:51.470 --> 01:03:53.753
But these days, you can be
the smartest guy in the room,

01:03:53.755 --> 01:03:56.076
the most qualified and no one cares.

01:03:56.291 --> 01:03:59.705
Unless you're flying around with a cape
or shooting lasers from your hands,

01:03:59.794 --> 01:04:02.377
no one will even listen.

01:04:04.424 --> 01:04:05.246
Well,

01:04:05.897 --> 01:04:07.956
I've got a cape and lasers.

01:04:08.845 --> 01:04:10.928
With our technology and with EDITH,

01:04:11.118 --> 01:04:15.884
Mysterio will be
the greatest hero on Earth!

01:04:15.977 --> 01:04:17.058
Yeah!

01:04:17.145 --> 01:04:19.808
Then everyone will listen!

01:04:21.772 --> 01:04:24.618
Not to a boozy man-child.

01:04:24.788 --> 01:04:26.145
No!

01:04:26.338 --> 01:04:28.958
Not to a hormonal teenager.

01:04:28.966 --> 01:04:30.407
No!

01:04:31.034 --> 01:04:31.960
To me...

01:04:32.473 --> 01:04:35.411
and to my very wealthy crew.

01:04:35.914 --> 01:04:37.746
To us.
To us.

01:04:37.832 --> 01:04:39.309
To Mysterio!

01:04:39.440 --> 01:04:40.826
To Mysterio!

01:04:40.919 --> 01:04:42.316
To Peter Parker.

01:04:42.388 --> 01:04:44.140
To Peter Parker!

01:04:45.131 --> 01:04:46.167
Poor kid.

01:04:47.926 --> 01:04:49.133
Let's get to work.

01:04:53.556 --> 01:04:55.343
Peter, oh my God.
Hey. Hey.

01:04:55.592 --> 01:04:57.881
We almost died.
It's fine. It's fine.

01:04:57.983 --> 01:04:59.510
Hey, I swear, I'm done with the mission.

01:04:59.991 --> 01:05:01.846
Dude, the trip's over.
What?

01:05:02.045 --> 01:05:04.079
There's monsters coming out
of the ground everywhere we go.

01:05:04.109 --> 01:05:05.649
Of course our parents
would want us home.

01:05:05.714 --> 01:05:08.833
Please don't put me on hold.
Peter, you're not dead.

01:05:08.927 --> 01:05:10.780
Oh my God. Yes, good.

01:05:10.872 --> 01:05:12.554
Stay here. Don't...
Put some clothes on.

01:05:12.659 --> 01:05:13.748
We're booking flights.

01:05:13.952 --> 01:05:16.194
We came for science,
we're leaving because of witches.

01:05:16.287 --> 01:05:17.846
Welcome to the new Dark Ages.

01:05:20.060 --> 01:05:21.479
What is going on, dude?

01:05:21.481 --> 01:05:22.676
We're going home in the morning.

01:05:22.847 --> 01:05:24.629
No, no. All the Elementals are gone.

01:05:24.811 --> 01:05:25.656
Ned.

01:05:26.048 --> 01:05:27.067
Coming, sweetie.

01:05:27.465 --> 01:05:28.979
Hey, can you guys keep it down?

01:05:28.981 --> 01:05:29.991
I'm live-streaming.

01:05:31.719 --> 01:05:32.566
Yeah.

01:05:33.099 --> 01:05:33.710
Hey.

01:05:34.764 --> 01:05:35.408
Hey.

01:05:35.792 --> 01:05:36.855
Where were you?

01:05:37.760 --> 01:05:38.895
I got lost.

01:05:39.287 --> 01:05:40.650
We were worried about you.

01:05:41.646 --> 01:05:42.588
Good thing you're back.

01:05:43.466 --> 01:05:44.250
Yeah.

01:05:44.774 --> 01:05:46.091
So much for Paris.

01:05:46.669 --> 01:05:47.799
It would have been fun.

01:05:47.801 --> 01:05:48.307
Yeah.

01:05:48.996 --> 01:05:50.257
Night.
Night.

01:05:52.142 --> 01:05:53.009
You look ni...

01:06:00.707 --> 01:06:01.478
ok.

01:06:03.835 --> 01:06:04.704
Hey.
Hey.

01:06:06.117 --> 01:06:06.857
Look...

01:06:07.964 --> 01:06:10.390
I'm not ready for this trip
to be over yet and...

01:06:10.977 --> 01:06:12.756
I kind of want to do something fun

01:06:13.189 --> 01:06:16.893
that's not on the itinerary or planned
or with Mr. Harrington.

01:06:16.895 --> 01:06:17.730
Yes.

01:06:18.683 --> 01:06:20.800
Yes, like you wanna go?

01:06:21.292 --> 01:06:21.965
Yes.

01:06:23.578 --> 01:06:24.487
Ok, awesome.

01:06:24.489 --> 01:06:25.935
I'll see you outside in ten minutes.

01:06:26.258 --> 01:06:27.491
Meet me outside in five minutes.

01:06:29.171 --> 01:06:30.225
Five is good.
Ok.

01:06:30.770 --> 01:06:31.868
Ok, bye.
Bye.

01:06:35.909 --> 01:06:38.902
<i>Night Monkey, help us!
Help! Night Monkey!</i>

01:06:48.137 --> 01:06:49.007
Hey.
Hey.

01:06:49.083 --> 01:06:50.288
So, where do you wanna go?

01:06:50.381 --> 01:06:52.326
Who cares?
Awesome.

01:06:52.388 --> 01:06:53.388
Ok.
Let's go.

01:07:00.271 --> 01:07:02.550
I'm glad we're doing this.
Yeah, me too.

01:07:02.644 --> 01:07:04.276
To see the city a bit.

01:07:05.187 --> 01:07:07.742
They used to execute people
on this bridge.

01:07:07.899 --> 01:07:11.599
They would put them in a basket,
and they would drown in the water.

01:07:14.077 --> 01:07:16.034
Sorry.
It's ok.

01:07:19.392 --> 01:07:22.844
There's this thing I've been wanting
to talk to you about

01:07:23.043 --> 01:07:24.955
for a while.

01:07:26.709 --> 01:07:27.548
Yeah?

01:07:29.157 --> 01:07:30.773
It's our last night in Europe,

01:07:30.783 --> 01:07:33.034
and I had this plan that I wanted to...

01:07:33.511 --> 01:07:34.390
tell you.

01:07:34.801 --> 01:07:36.337
I'm justl'm just gonna tell you.

01:07:38.680 --> 01:07:40.637
MJ, I...
I'm Spider-Man.

01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:43.203
What?

01:07:43.296 --> 01:07:45.054
That's what you were gonna say.
That you're Spider-Man.

01:07:46.688 --> 01:07:47.478
No.

01:07:48.533 --> 01:07:49.746
I'm not Spider-Man.

01:07:50.292 --> 01:07:53.056
I mean, I've been watching you
for like a while now.

01:07:53.722 --> 01:07:55.191
It's kind of obvious.

01:07:56.417 --> 01:07:57.417
I'm not Spider-Man.

01:07:57.419 --> 01:07:59.832
I mean, what would make you think
that I was Spider-Man?

01:07:59.867 --> 01:08:01.904
Peter, Washington?
Yeah?

01:08:01.995 --> 01:08:05.875
The fact that you, like disappear
out of nowhere for no reason.

01:08:06.031 --> 01:08:09.003
No, I was sick. Remember?
I had my... The tummy?

01:08:09.005 --> 01:08:10.712
You know Susan Yang
thinks you're a male escort.

01:08:10.714 --> 01:08:12.920
What? No, of course
I'm not a male escort.

01:08:12.922 --> 01:08:13.912
Well, then you're Spider-Man.

01:08:13.914 --> 01:08:15.916
No, I'm not Spider-Man at all.

01:08:16.239 --> 01:08:17.253
Then what about tonight?

01:08:17.255 --> 01:08:18.889
You snuck off, and you fought that thing.

01:08:18.891 --> 01:08:19.513
I saw you.

01:08:19.515 --> 01:08:21.928
You can't have seen me
because I'm not Spider-Man.

01:08:21.931 --> 01:08:24.473
And also, on the news,
it was the Night Monkey.

01:08:24.840 --> 01:08:26.087
The Night Monkey?
Yeah.

01:08:26.089 --> 01:08:27.655
That's what it said on the news,

01:08:28.146 --> 01:08:30.690
and the news never lies.

01:08:31.733 --> 01:08:33.214
Night Monkey. Ok.

01:08:33.872 --> 01:08:34.855
What are you doing?

01:08:36.771 --> 01:08:39.422
Well, do the Night Monkey
and Spider-Man use the same webs?

01:08:41.200 --> 01:08:42.407
I mean, maybe.

01:08:42.915 --> 01:08:44.566
Maybe he's a Spider Monkey.
Who knows?

01:08:49.591 --> 01:08:52.208
Were you only watching me
because you thought I was Spider-Man?

01:08:55.676 --> 01:08:56.574
Yeah.

01:08:57.800 --> 01:08:59.328
Why else would I be watching you?

01:09:01.846 --> 01:09:02.970
Doesn't matter.

01:09:03.947 --> 01:09:05.245
Just thought that maybe...

01:09:10.907 --> 01:09:12.099
What the hell was that?

01:09:13.900 --> 01:09:14.981
I don't know.

01:09:26.204 --> 01:09:28.742
What is it, like some kind of projector
or something?

01:09:29.161 --> 01:09:30.375
Yeah, but it's...

01:09:30.871 --> 01:09:32.304
really advanced.

01:09:32.969 --> 01:09:34.671
It... It looked so real.

01:09:34.673 --> 01:09:35.475
It...

01:09:35.656 --> 01:09:37.024
Yeah, really real.

01:09:38.048 --> 01:09:39.546
Wait, does that mean that?

01:09:39.674 --> 01:09:41.102
The Elementals are fake?

01:09:41.913 --> 01:09:44.186
That doesn't make any sense
because we were there, right?

01:09:44.681 --> 01:09:46.484
There was fire and destruction,

01:09:46.876 --> 01:09:47.538
and...

01:09:49.502 --> 01:09:50.806
Who would do something like that?

01:10:00.613 --> 01:10:01.774
Mysterio.

01:10:06.744 --> 01:10:08.110
I am Spider-Man.

01:10:09.247 --> 01:10:10.638
And I've really messed up.

01:10:10.724 --> 01:10:11.579
Wait.

01:10:11.636 --> 01:10:13.075
You're being serious right now?

01:10:13.610 --> 01:10:15.457
You're not joking with me,
like you're 100 percent serious?

01:10:15.459 --> 01:10:16.270
Because it's not funny.

01:10:16.309 --> 01:10:17.086
No, I'm not joking.

01:10:17.180 --> 01:10:19.430
Because I was...
I was only like 67 percent sure.

01:10:19.432 --> 01:10:21.584
I... So why, why are you here?
MJ.

01:10:21.586 --> 01:10:24.343
Why? Why are you on this school trip?
MJ, look..I know you have a lot of questions,

01:10:24.476 --> 01:10:26.217
but look, but we have to get out of here, ok?

01:10:26.264 --> 01:10:29.577
Ok. Ok. I can't believe I figured it out!

01:10:31.782 --> 01:10:33.306
You took everything from me!

01:10:34.522 --> 01:10:36.058
This is for my family!

01:10:42.739 --> 01:10:43.900
Pause.

01:10:45.867 --> 01:10:46.867
Pause.

01:10:47.994 --> 01:10:48.925
Sorry.

01:10:49.537 --> 01:10:52.120
Yeah, can you just fast-forward
to the end?

01:10:52.206 --> 01:10:53.242
Yep. Stand by.

01:10:57.920 --> 01:11:00.450
Alright, fly, fly, fly, zap, zap, zap.

01:11:00.882 --> 01:11:01.743
Pause.

01:11:02.399 --> 01:11:04.376
I'm not in love with this choreography,
but it'll do.

01:11:04.469 --> 01:11:05.243
Kill image.

01:11:06.214 --> 01:11:07.294
De-cloak drones.

01:11:09.390 --> 01:11:10.391
Alright, weapons.

01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:12.393
You want to weaponize?
Yep.

01:11:12.643 --> 01:11:14.384
Weapons only. Stand by.

01:11:23.553 --> 01:11:24.378
<i>Nice.</i>

01:11:25.178 --> 01:11:25.858
Stop.

01:11:27.047 --> 01:11:29.324
Something. I don't know what it is.
It's something...

01:11:29.410 --> 01:11:30.733
Just dou... You know what?

01:11:32.033 --> 01:11:33.872
Double the damage
and then run it again.

01:11:34.349 --> 01:11:35.671
<i>You want me to double it up?</i>

01:11:35.728 --> 01:11:37.094
Yeah.
<i>Alright.</i>

01:11:37.356 --> 01:11:38.293
Cover your ears.

01:11:47.707 --> 01:11:49.573
That is good! That's good.

01:11:50.563 --> 01:11:52.243
We on schedule?
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:11:52.432 --> 01:11:54.717
<i>Uploading software hack
to EDITH network.</i>

01:11:54.898 --> 01:11:58.312
<i>With her drones, we'll create an event
big enough to cover an entire city.</i>

01:11:58.402 --> 01:11:59.313
Alright, well done.

01:11:59.377 --> 01:12:01.960
Make sure every drone is weapons-hot.
We need maximum damage.

01:12:02.015 --> 01:12:04.109
That is gonna cause a lot of casualties.

01:12:04.110 --> 01:12:04.728
Yeah.

01:12:04.729 --> 01:12:07.376
More casualties, more coverage.
I got to cut through the static.

01:12:07.477 --> 01:12:10.319
London is a beautiful city,
and it will suffer but they can rebuild.

01:12:10.321 --> 01:12:12.132
I mean if I'm the next Iron Man,

01:12:12.202 --> 01:12:15.113
I need to save the world
from an Avengers level threat.

01:12:16.332 --> 01:12:17.014
But...

01:12:17.239 --> 01:12:19.750
when its new savior descends,

01:12:19.924 --> 01:12:22.462
all those casualties will be forgotten.

01:12:23.105 --> 01:12:25.916
Janice, you'll be in position with my
quick-change armor for the victory lap?

01:12:26.259 --> 01:12:27.571
Of course. Do you wanna

01:12:27.655 --> 01:12:28.794
try?
No, no, that's...

01:12:28.948 --> 01:12:30.559
What's going on with my hand?
Why is that happening?

01:12:32.174 --> 01:12:35.059
One of the drones that came back
from the plaza was missing a projector.

01:12:35.061 --> 01:12:35.850
It's fine.

01:12:36.234 --> 01:12:37.047
Wait, and you're...

01:12:37.511 --> 01:12:39.046
You're telling me this now?

01:12:39.647 --> 01:12:41.096
<i>It's... It's one drone.</i>

01:12:41.357 --> 01:12:43.000
<i>The image will be perfect, I promise.</i>

01:12:43.002 --> 01:12:44.192
That projector is evidence.

01:12:44.427 --> 01:12:46.557
It's going to tell people what we're doing
and how we're doing it.

01:12:47.791 --> 01:12:51.114
I am trying to fool 7 billion people here,
including Nick Fury,

01:12:51.172 --> 01:12:54.631
who happens to be the most paranoid
and most dangerous person on the planet.

01:12:54.868 --> 01:12:56.615
And if he catches on
before I've killed him,

01:12:56.617 --> 01:12:57.914
he will put a bullet in my head.

01:12:57.999 --> 01:13:00.332
And nobody wants a bullet
in their head, right?

01:13:02.587 --> 01:13:03.587
Right?

01:13:06.090 --> 01:13:07.956
William, can you look at me?

01:13:10.136 --> 01:13:11.252
Pull up EDITH.

01:13:13.390 --> 01:13:14.390
<i>Hello, Quentin.</i>

01:13:14.392 --> 01:13:17.893
Yeah. Hi, honey. I need a level-five search,
full-resource protocol for this device.

01:13:18.344 --> 01:13:19.380
<i>Magnifying.</i>

01:13:20.748 --> 01:13:22.979
There. Search everything going in
and out of that building.

01:13:24.108 --> 01:13:25.108
<i>Located.</i>

01:13:26.777 --> 01:13:27.777
Shit.

01:13:30.990 --> 01:13:32.061
You know William,

01:13:32.378 --> 01:13:33.028
one day,

01:13:33.272 --> 01:13:35.688
after I've had to kill Peter Parker
because of this,

01:13:35.991 --> 01:13:37.127
I hope you remember,

01:13:37.248 --> 01:13:38.329
that his blood,

01:13:38.331 --> 01:13:39.747
is on your hands!

01:13:43.068 --> 01:13:45.365
I can't believe I gave Beck
those glasses.

01:13:45.367 --> 01:13:46.583
I mean, how could I be that stupid?

01:13:46.585 --> 01:13:50.074
He's probably spying on me right now
or sending a drone to come and kill me.

01:13:50.301 --> 01:13:52.918
You had access to killer drones?

01:13:53.012 --> 01:13:56.058
Yeah, I didn't really want them,
especially after I almost killed Brad.

01:13:56.676 --> 01:13:58.010
You almost killed Brad?

01:13:58.301 --> 01:14:01.512
Look, I have to call Mr. Fury
and tell him that Beck's a fraud but...

01:14:02.376 --> 01:14:04.507
I think he tapped my phone.
Ok, so what are you gonna do?

01:14:05.443 --> 01:14:08.150
I need my suit and I have
to go to Berlin and...

01:14:08.391 --> 01:14:09.935
talk to Mr. Fury in person.

01:14:15.370 --> 01:14:15.864
Just...

01:14:35.752 --> 01:14:36.664
Ned, perfect.

01:14:37.301 --> 01:14:38.756
The costume looks great...

01:14:39.892 --> 01:14:41.627
for the costume party,

01:14:41.629 --> 01:14:42.324
at the...

01:14:42.874 --> 01:14:43.978
prince's castle.

01:14:43.980 --> 01:14:45.266
She knows. I told her.

01:14:46.107 --> 01:14:47.769
He didn't tell me. I figured it out.

01:14:50.969 --> 01:14:52.686
That's cool.
Like, a long time ago.

01:14:54.365 --> 01:14:55.907
Look, Mysterio is a fraud.

01:14:56.606 --> 01:14:58.360
But he saved me and Betty's lives.

01:14:58.452 --> 01:15:00.660
He's been faking the whole thing
with illusion tech.

01:15:00.662 --> 01:15:03.065
Yeah, he's using these, like,
hologram projectors.

01:15:03.749 --> 01:15:04.467
That's...

01:15:05.147 --> 01:15:05.867
crazy.

01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:06.744
Yeah.

01:15:09.155 --> 01:15:12.289
So you guys were working
the case together or what?

01:15:12.383 --> 01:15:13.383
It's been mostly me.

01:15:14.265 --> 01:15:16.709
Look Ned, I need you to call May,
get her to call Mr. Harrington,

01:15:16.713 --> 01:15:19.382
say she wanted me to stay with family
in Berlin until all this blows over, ok?

01:15:19.515 --> 01:15:20.681
Got it. Easy.

01:15:21.355 --> 01:15:23.219
You guys lie with such ease.

01:15:23.978 --> 01:15:24.806
I got to go.

01:15:25.169 --> 01:15:27.057
Wait, wait, wait. The projector.

01:15:27.445 --> 01:15:28.637
You're gonna need this.

01:15:29.692 --> 01:15:31.406
Don't tell anyone about this, ok?

01:15:31.408 --> 01:15:32.712
Anyone who knows is in danger.

01:15:41.214 --> 01:15:42.370
So you know too.

01:15:43.200 --> 01:15:43.882
It's cool.

01:15:43.958 --> 01:15:47.167
I've known first, and I've known longer,
but it's not a competition.

01:16:09.157 --> 01:16:10.518
Excuse me. Do you know where?

01:16:10.892 --> 01:16:11.527
Nacht Monkey!

01:16:11.529 --> 01:16:12.817
No, wait, I didn't...

01:16:13.069 --> 01:16:13.808
Oh man.

01:16:16.889 --> 01:16:17.781
Get in.

01:16:24.345 --> 01:16:25.093
Mr. Fury...

01:16:25.095 --> 01:16:27.525
You've got a lot of explaining to do.

01:16:27.626 --> 01:16:29.788
No, no, no, listen.
Wait until we're secure.

01:16:30.377 --> 01:16:31.180
Ok.

01:16:36.842 --> 01:16:37.704
Right.

01:17:03.440 --> 01:17:04.325
So...

01:17:05.105 --> 01:17:07.496
is there anything you want
to tell us about your girlfriend?

01:17:07.809 --> 01:17:08.989
He's talking about EDITH.

01:17:09.274 --> 01:17:12.413
Look, I know I made a mistake and I'm sorry,
but he is not who you think he is.

01:17:12.444 --> 01:17:15.059
Beck is a liar.
Mysterio, the Elementals, it's all fake.

01:17:15.061 --> 01:17:16.552
He has some sort of illusion tech.

01:17:16.841 --> 01:17:19.504
That's how he tricked you guys
and tricked me into giving him EDITH.

01:17:20.052 --> 01:17:21.536
It's a projector.

01:17:22.176 --> 01:17:23.661
I pulled it off the fire monster in Prague.

01:17:23.722 --> 01:17:27.056
So all that death
and destruction we witnessed

01:17:27.143 --> 01:17:28.759
was created by this?

01:17:28.853 --> 01:17:30.970
No, not just this.
I think he's using drones.

01:17:31.756 --> 01:17:36.233
Well, if this is true, then Beck's
very dangerous and we need to be smart.

01:17:36.521 --> 01:17:37.975
Who else did you tell about this?

01:17:38.904 --> 01:17:39.879
Parker?

01:17:40.398 --> 01:17:41.238
Parker!

01:17:41.240 --> 01:17:42.256
What's wrong?

01:17:42.563 --> 01:17:43.819
It's Beck. He's here.

01:17:44.368 --> 01:17:45.268
What?

01:17:45.700 --> 01:17:46.499
Hill?

01:17:51.978 --> 01:17:52.963
No, it's just an illu...

01:17:54.378 --> 01:17:55.414
Fury!

01:18:01.294 --> 01:18:01.810
<i>Peter.</i>

01:18:03.416 --> 01:18:04.650
<i>I thought we were close.</i>

01:18:05.433 --> 01:18:07.613
<i>Fury always had to die,</i>

01:18:07.615 --> 01:18:08.846
<i>but not you.</i>

01:18:09.199 --> 01:18:10.168
Stop hiding, Beck!

01:18:12.813 --> 01:18:14.805
<i>I tried to help you walk away.</i>

01:18:15.195 --> 01:18:16.850
<i>Now you're making me do this.</i>

01:18:21.439 --> 01:18:24.147
<i>You told me, you were just a kid.</i>

01:18:25.590 --> 01:18:26.938
<i>You told me,</i>

01:18:26.940 --> 01:18:28.956
<i>you wanted to run after that girl.</i>

01:18:28.958 --> 01:18:30.271
<i>Help me!</i>
MJ!

01:18:31.832 --> 01:18:32.913
God!

01:18:34.919 --> 01:18:36.741
Peter, what's going on?

01:18:37.002 --> 01:18:38.038
I know this isn't real.

01:18:38.464 --> 01:18:39.464
<i>Do you, though?</i>

01:18:41.008 --> 01:18:41.825
MJ!

01:18:42.835 --> 01:18:43.489
MJ!

01:18:46.847 --> 01:18:49.339
<i>I don't think you know what's real, Peter.</i>

01:19:02.613 --> 01:19:03.899
<i>You need to wake up!</i>

01:19:27.363 --> 01:19:29.338
<i>I mean, look at yourself.</i>

01:19:39.275 --> 01:19:41.880
<i>You are just a scared little kid,</i>

01:19:42.202 --> 01:19:43.770
<i>in a sweat suit.</i>

01:19:44.989 --> 01:19:49.654
<i>I created Mysterio to give the world
someone to believe in.</i>

01:19:50.119 --> 01:19:51.530
<i>I control the truth.</i>

01:19:51.620 --> 01:19:54.363
<i>Mysterio is the truth.</i>

01:20:17.980 --> 01:20:19.553
<i>If you were good enough,</i>

01:20:20.084 --> 01:20:21.895
<i>maybe Tony would still be alive.</i>

01:20:34.663 --> 01:20:37.872
<i>Deep down, you know I'm right.</i>

01:20:49.011 --> 01:20:51.301
<i>You made your choice.</i>

01:20:51.618 --> 01:20:53.427
<i>And all you had to do
was step aside.</i>

01:20:54.641 --> 01:20:57.303
<i>And now you have...</i>

01:21:09.504 --> 01:21:10.141
Fury.

01:21:10.991 --> 01:21:12.249
Beck's people,

01:21:12.368 --> 01:21:13.525
are trying to find,

01:21:13.917 --> 01:21:15.637
everyone who could expose him.

01:21:17.033 --> 01:21:18.033
Who'd you tell?

01:21:18.513 --> 01:21:20.821
I know you told someone,
so just tell me.

01:21:20.823 --> 01:21:22.458
Ok.
Who did you tell?

01:21:22.833 --> 01:21:25.684
Who else did you tell?
Just Ned and MJ from my class.

01:21:25.982 --> 01:21:28.034
Maybe Ned told his girlfriend Betty,
but that's it.

01:21:29.801 --> 01:21:30.560
What?

01:21:30.890 --> 01:21:33.175
You are so gullible.

01:21:33.813 --> 01:21:34.502
What?

01:21:34.699 --> 01:21:35.788
You're smart as a whip.

01:21:35.974 --> 01:21:36.974
Just a...

01:21:38.060 --> 01:21:38.930
sucker.

01:21:39.978 --> 01:21:42.265
And now all your friends have to die.
Oh my God.

01:21:47.239 --> 01:21:50.020
It's easy to fool people when
they're already fooling themselves.

01:21:55.576 --> 01:21:56.893
But for what it's worth, Peter,

01:21:58.831 --> 01:22:00.072
I really am sorry.

01:22:09.846 --> 01:22:11.114
EDITH.
<i>Yes, Quentin.</i>

01:22:11.155 --> 01:22:13.430
Access files to Peter Parker's class trip.

01:22:14.847 --> 01:22:16.588
I need them to fly home from London.

01:22:56.305 --> 01:22:57.305
Hi.

01:22:58.474 --> 01:22:59.510
Where am I?

01:22:59.892 --> 01:23:01.672
Municipal holding facility.

01:23:02.060 --> 01:23:04.518
They said they found you
unconscious at the train yard.

01:23:04.902 --> 01:23:05.771
Very dangerous.

01:23:06.099 --> 01:23:08.914
And we gave you the shirt
because you seemed a bit cold.

01:23:09.568 --> 01:23:10.418
Thanks.

01:23:12.977 --> 01:23:14.058
You guys are nice.

01:23:15.240 --> 01:23:17.072
You speak really good English.

01:23:17.576 --> 01:23:18.942
Welcome to the Netherlands.

01:23:20.103 --> 01:23:21.517
I'm in the Netherlands right now?

01:23:21.610 --> 01:23:22.329
Yep.

01:23:24.330 --> 01:23:25.023
Bye.

01:23:26.028 --> 01:23:26.918
Guard!

01:23:27.508 --> 01:23:29.734
The guard is on a break.
Probably talking to his wife.

01:23:29.736 --> 01:23:31.648
Yeah, she's pregnant.
Yeah?

01:23:31.687 --> 01:23:32.538
Yeah.

01:23:40.557 --> 01:23:41.638
Yeah.

01:23:42.392 --> 01:23:43.152
Yeah.

01:23:44.183 --> 01:23:45.072
Night Monkey.

01:23:45.375 --> 01:23:46.036
Yeah.

01:23:50.877 --> 01:23:52.038
You guys ok?

01:24:04.563 --> 01:24:06.018
Excuse me, sir?
Yeah?

01:24:06.020 --> 01:24:08.228
Could I borrow your phone?
Yeah.

01:24:08.229 --> 01:24:08.928
Take care.

01:24:09.724 --> 01:24:11.077
Everyone is so nice here.

01:24:12.675 --> 01:24:13.457
Ok.

01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:19.720
Ok.

01:24:21.598 --> 01:24:23.806
Pick up, pick up, pick up. Hey, hey...

01:24:25.917 --> 01:24:28.027
I messed up. I need a...
I need a ride.

01:24:29.398 --> 01:24:30.387
Where am I?

01:24:30.753 --> 01:24:31.686
Where am I, sir?

01:24:31.907 --> 01:24:33.230
It's Broek op Langedijk.

01:24:35.862 --> 01:24:37.899
Hang on.
Could you say that into there?

01:24:37.990 --> 01:24:41.037
Hi. It's Broek op Langedijk here.

01:24:42.012 --> 01:24:42.950
Yeah, no problem.

01:24:43.996 --> 01:24:44.618
Thanks.

01:24:45.622 --> 01:24:46.622
Did you get that?

01:25:08.259 --> 01:25:08.940
Peter?

01:25:09.498 --> 01:25:10.554
Are you ok?

01:25:10.826 --> 01:25:12.040
Happy, is that you?

01:25:12.209 --> 01:25:13.646
Is it me... yeah, of course it's me.

01:25:13.787 --> 01:25:14.567
Stop!

01:25:15.492 --> 01:25:17.153
Tell me something only you would know.

01:25:17.487 --> 01:25:18.515
Only I would know...

01:25:20.062 --> 01:25:21.854
Remember when we went to Germany?

01:25:22.081 --> 01:25:23.849
You pay-per-viewed a video
in your room?

01:25:24.098 --> 01:25:26.051
They didn't list the titles,
but I could tell by the price,

01:25:26.053 --> 01:25:27.627
it was an adult film at the front desk.

01:25:27.683 --> 01:25:28.957
And you didn't know how I knew...
Ok, ok.

01:25:28.994 --> 01:25:30.559
Fine! It's you. It's you. Stop.

01:25:33.670 --> 01:25:35.127
It's so good to see you.

01:25:36.685 --> 01:25:38.666
Peter, you're going to have to tell me
what the hell is going on here.

01:25:40.173 --> 01:25:41.382
Ok, hold still.

01:25:41.678 --> 01:25:42.885
There we go.

01:25:50.696 --> 01:25:51.994
I thought you had super strength.

01:25:52.222 --> 01:25:53.204
It still hurts.

01:25:55.942 --> 01:25:58.059
Happy, come on.
Alright, relax.

01:26:00.030 --> 01:26:02.113
Just a few more. There we go.
Oh my God, Happy.

01:26:02.255 --> 01:26:03.042
Relax.

01:26:03.044 --> 01:26:04.255
Don't tell me to relax, Happy!

01:26:04.257 --> 01:26:06.553
How can I relax
when I messed up so bad?

01:26:07.415 --> 01:26:08.566
I trusted Beck.

01:26:09.013 --> 01:26:09.761
Right?

01:26:10.094 --> 01:26:13.633
I thought he was my friend. So I gave him
the only thing Mr. Stark left behind for me,

01:26:13.635 --> 01:26:15.863
and now he's gonna kill my friends
and half of Europe,

01:26:15.865 --> 01:26:18.280
so please do not tell me to relax.

01:26:20.646 --> 01:26:22.709
I'm sorry, Happy. I'm sorry.
I should not shout.

01:26:26.584 --> 01:26:27.772
I just really miss him.

01:26:28.934 --> 01:26:30.175
Yeah, I miss him too.

01:26:33.430 --> 01:26:34.650
Everywhere I go...

01:26:36.067 --> 01:26:37.293
I see his face.

01:26:37.526 --> 01:26:38.287
And...

01:26:38.751 --> 01:26:41.884
the whole world is asking who's
gonna be the next Iron Man and...

01:26:44.966 --> 01:26:47.451
I don't know if that's me, Happy.
I'm not Iron Man.

01:26:50.122 --> 01:26:51.329
You're not Iron Man.

01:26:52.527 --> 01:26:54.248
You're never gonna be Iron Man.

01:26:56.360 --> 01:26:57.923
Nobody could live up to Tony.

01:26:58.830 --> 01:26:59.972
Not even Tony.

01:27:01.696 --> 01:27:02.898
Tony was my best friend.

01:27:03.757 --> 01:27:04.873
And he was a mess.

01:27:05.428 --> 01:27:08.300
He second-guessed everything he did.
He was all over the place.

01:27:09.388 --> 01:27:12.301
The one thing that he did that he didn't
second-guess was picking you.

01:27:14.563 --> 01:27:17.186
I don't think Tony
would have done what he did,

01:27:18.102 --> 01:27:20.942
if he didn't know that you were
gonna be here after he was gone.

01:27:23.029 --> 01:27:24.388
Now, your friends are in trouble,

01:27:24.738 --> 01:27:25.879
you're all alone,

01:27:26.068 --> 01:27:27.362
your tech is missing.

01:27:29.356 --> 01:27:30.621
What are you gonna do about it?

01:27:36.334 --> 01:27:37.675
I'm gonna kick his ass.

01:27:38.139 --> 01:27:39.538
But I mean, I mean, I mean right now.

01:27:39.683 --> 01:27:41.142
Like specifically
what are we gonna do?

01:27:41.144 --> 01:27:43.881
Because we've been hovering over
a tulip field for the last 15 minutes.

01:27:43.967 --> 01:27:46.880
Right. I can't call my friends
because he's tracking their phones.

01:27:47.495 --> 01:27:48.406
Give me your phone.

01:27:48.638 --> 01:27:49.879
My cell phone?
Yeah.

01:27:49.973 --> 01:27:51.464
Ok. Here.

01:27:52.016 --> 01:27:53.945
What's your password?
Password.

01:27:54.366 --> 01:27:55.759
No, what is your password?

01:27:55.761 --> 01:27:57.550
Password, the word spelled out,
password.

01:27:57.552 --> 01:27:59.655
Head of security,
and your password is password?

01:27:59.657 --> 01:28:00.884
I don't feel good about it either.

01:28:00.942 --> 01:28:03.275
<i>Hello, governor.
Cup of tea for you?</i>

01:28:03.277 --> 01:28:04.154
<i>I'm gonna be in London soon.</i>

01:28:04.163 --> 01:28:05.894
They're in London.
London, ok.

01:28:06.156 --> 01:28:08.148
Yeah, I need a suit.
Suit?

01:28:29.987 --> 01:28:30.753
Ok...

01:28:31.890 --> 01:28:34.382
bring up everything you have
on Spider-Man.

01:28:41.525 --> 01:28:42.530
Yeah, open that.

01:28:42.774 --> 01:28:44.431
Ok, no, no, no.

01:28:51.752 --> 01:28:52.752
What?

01:28:52.869 --> 01:28:53.622
Nothing.

01:28:54.412 --> 01:28:56.904
You take care of the suit.
I'll take care of the music.

01:29:01.353 --> 01:29:02.911
I love Led Zeppelin.

01:29:08.914 --> 01:29:10.528
Ok, can you pull up my web-shooters?

01:29:12.347 --> 01:29:13.584
Isolate the Taser webs,

01:29:13.586 --> 01:29:15.264
and reconfigure and boost,

01:29:15.584 --> 01:29:17.746
the voltage to a factor of...

01:29:17.873 --> 01:29:22.013
25 percent and give me complete
manual control over detonation.

01:29:25.294 --> 01:29:28.443
I thought Kree having sleeper cells
was top secret information.

01:29:28.445 --> 01:29:29.098
Nick,

01:29:29.476 --> 01:29:31.227
satellites are picking up an EM pulse.

01:29:31.458 --> 01:29:32.685
I thought that was over.

01:29:32.832 --> 01:29:34.451
It's the biggest one yet.
Where?

01:29:35.072 --> 01:29:35.864
London.

01:29:36.020 --> 01:29:38.347
Ok guys, the company set up a city tour,

01:29:38.349 --> 01:29:40.744
and then we'll grab a bite
and head to the airport.

01:29:43.894 --> 01:29:46.003
Is no one else going
to acknowledge how crazy this is?

01:29:46.021 --> 01:29:47.307
Yeah, I get it.

01:29:47.545 --> 01:29:50.162
There's been nothing scientific
about this science tour at all.

01:29:50.346 --> 01:29:51.899
No, no, no..
I'm talking about Peter.

01:29:52.001 --> 01:29:53.928
Has no one else here noticed
how shady he is?

01:29:54.014 --> 01:29:56.403
Because I saw him in the back
room of a rest stop with some...

01:29:56.436 --> 01:29:57.814
woman in his underwear,

01:29:57.816 --> 01:30:00.443
and he's always sneaking away,
like back at the opera?

01:30:01.423 --> 01:30:03.022
And now he's suddenly off the trip,

01:30:03.045 --> 01:30:04.731
with his family in Berlin?

01:30:04.733 --> 01:30:07.191
Is no one else interested in the truth?

01:30:08.700 --> 01:30:12.161
The very concept of objective truth
is fading out of the world.

01:30:12.449 --> 01:30:13.485
George Orwell.

01:30:13.799 --> 01:30:14.885
Thank you, MJ.
Yeah.

01:30:14.964 --> 01:30:17.617
Well, I mean since Peter's
not really here to tell his truth,

01:30:17.979 --> 01:30:19.747
what about you, Brad?

01:30:19.771 --> 01:30:22.094
Why do you think it's cool to take
pictures of people in the bathroom?

01:30:22.096 --> 01:30:23.760
Yeah dude, what's that about?

01:30:23.895 --> 01:30:25.684
No, no, no, it wasn't like that. It was...

01:30:26.604 --> 01:30:29.483
I was trying to take a...
Let's just put all this craziness behind us

01:30:29.905 --> 01:30:32.767
and have a nice, peaceful afternoon.

01:30:32.963 --> 01:30:35.128
Sounds great, Mr. Harrington,
said the class.

01:30:35.483 --> 01:30:36.225
Ok.

01:30:37.325 --> 01:30:39.068
I'm gonna be a cool teacher right now.

01:30:39.838 --> 01:30:42.260
You got to stop doing that, ok?
It is weird.

01:30:42.684 --> 01:30:46.018
No more photos in the bathroom.
Urinal or stalls.

01:30:46.395 --> 01:30:46.906
Ok?

01:30:46.908 --> 01:30:48.093
Look at this, guys.
Mr. Harrington.

01:30:48.787 --> 01:30:49.360
Come along.

01:30:49.565 --> 01:30:50.879
We got a bus all to ourselves.

01:30:50.881 --> 01:30:52.774
Nice to see you all. Come along.

01:30:52.906 --> 01:30:54.943
I'll get this, yeah? Why not?
Thank you.

01:30:55.033 --> 01:30:56.610
Yeah. Thank you, brother.

01:30:57.077 --> 01:30:58.233
Alright.

01:30:59.096 --> 01:31:00.276
I have the kids.

01:31:04.836 --> 01:31:06.075
<i>I got here as fast as I could.</i>

01:31:06.169 --> 01:31:07.464
<i>I did a full perimeter sweep.</i>

01:31:08.123 --> 01:31:08.819
<i>Nothing.</i>

01:31:09.673 --> 01:31:10.673
Damn it.

01:31:13.051 --> 01:31:14.167
Pulse is spiking.

01:31:14.260 --> 01:31:15.399
<i>I'll take another look.</i>

01:31:15.487 --> 01:31:17.148
Soon as you see something, report.

01:31:18.000 --> 01:31:19.563
<i>You're all we've got, Beck.</i>

01:31:19.933 --> 01:31:22.740
If this is what I fear,
then God help us, Fury.

01:31:23.853 --> 01:31:25.060
God help us all.

01:31:26.675 --> 01:31:28.632
Ok, people, no Avengers coming.
We're good to go.

01:31:28.779 --> 01:31:30.436
<i>William, launch the drones.</i>

01:31:30.438 --> 01:31:31.508
Copy that, brother.

01:31:31.769 --> 01:31:34.965
<i>Drones are entering
the atmosphere weapons-hot.</i>

01:31:40.856 --> 01:31:43.141
Excellent. Janice?
Still working on the cape.

01:31:43.230 --> 01:31:46.036
I got to get those wrinkles out in a few hours.
I could literally be shaking hands with the queen.

01:31:46.266 --> 01:31:47.679
<i>Guterman?</i>
Almost in position.

01:31:47.804 --> 01:31:48.782
Ok. Hit it, Victoria.

01:31:48.969 --> 01:31:50.193
Increasing pulse.

01:31:52.539 --> 01:31:55.375
Whatever this thing is, it's 100 times
bigger than the previous ones.

01:31:55.468 --> 01:31:56.325
EDITH?

01:31:56.803 --> 01:31:57.739
<i>Yes, Quentin.</i>

01:31:58.739 --> 01:32:00.137
Show me my loose ends.

01:32:01.053 --> 01:32:03.758
Once the show's going,
execute the kill order on my command.

01:32:03.852 --> 01:32:05.078
<i>Copy.</i>
Alright.

01:32:05.205 --> 01:32:06.286
Start the show.

01:32:08.148 --> 01:32:10.231
Let's save the world, people.

01:32:12.444 --> 01:32:14.356
I don't like this. Something's definitely up.

01:32:15.405 --> 01:32:16.846
You're an FOS now.

01:32:17.330 --> 01:32:18.490
Friend of Spider-Man.

01:32:18.575 --> 01:32:21.033
And you have to remember,
just stay calm.

01:32:25.300 --> 01:32:26.656
That doesn't look good.

01:32:26.997 --> 01:32:29.032
But it's fake, so there is
nothing to worry about.

01:32:29.654 --> 01:32:32.288
And the kids are in the kill zone.

01:32:33.006 --> 01:32:34.372
<i>Great work, Guterman.</i>

01:32:37.177 --> 01:32:39.319
What?
<i>Happy here. Happy Hogan here.</i>

01:32:39.507 --> 01:32:40.644
I know. What do you want?

01:32:40.646 --> 01:32:42.618
<i>Over at Mr. Stark's,
going through his belongings.</i>

01:32:42.620 --> 01:32:44.746
<i>Apparently, there was a
surfboard that you left behind.</i>

01:32:44.748 --> 01:32:45.273
What?

01:32:45.275 --> 01:32:46.061
<i>People there said,</i>

01:32:46.063 --> 01:32:48.027
<i>they didn't think Nick Fury
was a surfer, but I said.</i>

01:32:48.050 --> 01:32:49.088
<i>Appearances can be deceiving.</i>

01:32:49.090 --> 01:32:52.025
It's not mine. And don't ever
call this number again.

01:33:00.436 --> 01:33:02.527
Ok, Fury's got the coded message.

01:33:03.384 --> 01:33:04.532
Your friends are at the Tower Bridge.

01:33:04.533 --> 01:33:05.033
Ok.

01:33:05.034 --> 01:33:06.667
Your boy called it London Bridge,
but I figured it out.

01:33:06.998 --> 01:33:09.115
I'm going to go scoop them up, ok?
Yeah.

01:33:09.209 --> 01:33:10.455
We're close.
We're close.

01:33:10.457 --> 01:33:11.784
How's the suit coming?
Almost done.

01:33:11.878 --> 01:33:13.961
Good.
Wait, wait. Before you go...

01:33:15.074 --> 01:33:17.502
if something happens to me,
could you please give this to MJ?

01:33:17.592 --> 01:33:18.756
You're gonna make it back.

01:33:18.758 --> 01:33:19.755
You'll give it to her yourself.

01:33:19.844 --> 01:33:21.299
Ok? You got this.
I got this.

01:33:21.304 --> 01:33:22.531
Now, walk me through it.

01:33:22.961 --> 01:33:24.292
I know it's illusion tech, right?

01:33:24.294 --> 01:33:27.466
All I have to do is get inside the illusion,
then I can take it down,

01:33:27.468 --> 01:33:30.339
find him, and he's just a guy,
so I can take EDITH right back.

01:33:30.362 --> 01:33:32.684
Right, but last time, you got hit by a train.

01:33:33.149 --> 01:33:35.363
True, but this time...

01:33:35.944 --> 01:33:37.176
How do I explain this?

01:33:37.738 --> 01:33:39.057
I have like a sixth sense.

01:33:39.201 --> 01:33:40.107
The Peter-tingle.

01:33:41.229 --> 01:33:42.477
That's what you're talking about, right?

01:33:42.718 --> 01:33:43.925
It's not working, though.

01:33:43.964 --> 01:33:45.554
I heard it wasn't working right now.

01:33:45.556 --> 01:33:46.567
Is it?
It is working.

01:33:46.723 --> 01:33:48.212
Well, I don't know if it's working.
Good.

01:33:48.220 --> 01:33:49.247
Ok, so you got the Peter-tingle.

01:33:49.348 --> 01:33:51.206
That's the plan.
I'm gonna go get your friends.

01:33:51.584 --> 01:33:53.313
You get that Peter-tingle back online.

01:33:54.134 --> 01:33:55.473
I got this. I got this.

01:34:09.650 --> 01:34:10.755
Cue the lightning.

01:34:11.045 --> 01:34:11.993
Cuing lightning.

01:34:17.771 --> 01:34:20.102
Sir, is it still safe on the top,
or should we all...

01:34:20.663 --> 01:34:21.688
come down?

01:34:22.001 --> 01:34:22.781
Oh my...

01:34:24.617 --> 01:34:27.399
What did the bus driver say?
Bus driver's gone.

01:34:27.704 --> 01:34:29.036
What?
Where?

01:34:29.264 --> 01:34:32.130
It's ok. Mr. Dell and I have it
under control!

01:34:32.132 --> 01:34:33.976
No. No. Don't drag me into this, Roger.

01:34:33.978 --> 01:34:35.732
I'm doing my best, Julius!

01:34:36.337 --> 01:34:37.030
Look...

01:34:37.475 --> 01:34:38.671
the witches are back.

01:34:38.756 --> 01:34:40.588
Oh my God, get off the bus!

01:34:45.889 --> 01:34:48.014
Ok. Ok, follow me, kids.

01:34:50.977 --> 01:34:52.388
Come on, let's go!

01:35:05.366 --> 01:35:08.273
Now, that is an Avengers-level threat.

01:35:25.053 --> 01:35:26.472
This way. This way!

01:35:26.888 --> 01:35:28.345
Ok. Ok.
My God!

01:35:28.744 --> 01:35:30.138
Flash!
Follow that cursed hand.

01:35:30.225 --> 01:35:31.841
This way, kids. Follow me.

01:35:31.935 --> 01:35:35.053
It's not real, it's not real!
Well, it looks pretty real to me!

01:35:35.146 --> 01:35:36.432
Follow me, kids!

01:35:37.482 --> 01:35:38.689
Earth, wind, fire, water.

01:35:39.119 --> 01:35:39.608
Oh no.

01:35:39.932 --> 01:35:41.689
They joined forces
like the Power Rangers.

01:35:42.104 --> 01:35:43.817
You're thinking of Voltron.
Who?

01:35:43.856 --> 01:35:45.437
Voltron! You're thinking of Voltron!

01:35:45.741 --> 01:35:47.318
Hey, look, it's Mysterio!

01:35:47.408 --> 01:35:48.615
He's gonna save us!

01:35:52.121 --> 01:35:53.701
Wait, if Mysterio knows we know...

01:35:53.998 --> 01:35:56.081
Then we're in danger.
Yeah, and so are they.

01:35:56.167 --> 01:35:56.874
We should go.

01:35:58.836 --> 01:35:59.836
Kill that witch!

01:36:01.974 --> 01:36:04.336
This is for my family!

01:36:06.216 --> 01:36:07.550
You should get somewhere safe, Fury.

01:36:07.949 --> 01:36:09.531
<i>I don't see this ending well.</i>

01:36:09.862 --> 01:36:11.473
I appreciate your concern,

01:36:11.674 --> 01:36:13.596
but I never leave my men behind.

01:36:15.436 --> 01:36:17.393
Alright, comms check.
Can you hear me, kid?

01:36:17.395 --> 01:36:20.106
I can. It's a little loud out here.
I like the new suit.

01:36:20.108 --> 01:36:20.988
Thanks.

01:36:22.069 --> 01:36:23.317
Peter, you sure that's not real?

01:36:23.319 --> 01:36:26.083
Yeah, it's just 100 times bigger
than I expected.

01:36:26.085 --> 01:36:26.983
Still the play?

01:36:27.448 --> 01:36:29.815
We need to get high enough
so Beck doesn't see me coming.

01:36:29.909 --> 01:36:30.657
Copy.

01:36:30.932 --> 01:36:31.964
<i>Stay sticky.</i>

01:36:34.914 --> 01:36:36.997
<i>Hey, Happy.
Yeah, kid. What is it?</i>

01:36:37.083 --> 01:36:39.362
We need to have a serious conversation
about you and my aunt!

01:36:54.725 --> 01:36:56.397
Beck, report!

01:36:56.686 --> 01:36:57.762
Hey Guterman, I need..

01:36:57.764 --> 01:36:59.195
I need a response.
Something quick and decisive.

01:36:59.312 --> 01:37:02.600
It's all the Elementals.
They're somehow merged into something...

01:37:02.650 --> 01:37:04.642
into something else.
Something more powerful.

01:37:04.736 --> 01:37:06.728
It's drawing energy from the Earth's core.

01:37:11.773 --> 01:37:13.367
See, now, that's some bullshit.

01:37:17.210 --> 01:37:18.210
Is that?

01:37:22.712 --> 01:37:24.001
Be ready for anything.

01:37:24.499 --> 01:37:25.253
Yeah.

01:37:31.554 --> 01:37:33.591
It's not real, it's not real, it's not real!

01:37:40.313 --> 01:37:41.474
That's awesome.

01:38:07.340 --> 01:38:09.332
William, I've got drones
breaking formation.

01:38:09.425 --> 01:38:11.240
Well, maybe they hit a
flock of birds or something.

01:38:11.242 --> 01:38:11.938
You're fine.

01:38:12.047 --> 01:38:14.117
Well, I wanna see what's happening there.
I'm taking manual control.

01:38:20.783 --> 01:38:22.170
<i>Do you see anything?</i>

01:38:22.814 --> 01:38:23.609
Yeah.

01:38:24.935 --> 01:38:25.853
And I'm gonna kill him.

01:38:30.488 --> 01:38:32.354
I hope this works.

01:38:48.548 --> 01:38:49.548
You got me?

01:38:54.637 --> 01:38:55.637
I got you.

01:38:56.291 --> 01:38:58.032
<i>Boss, the illusion is coming apart.</i>

01:39:01.561 --> 01:39:02.768
I see you.

01:39:06.732 --> 01:39:08.850
EDITH, give me some protection.
<i>Copy.</i>

01:39:23.644 --> 01:39:24.984
Hey kill it. Just kill the illusion.
Kill it.

01:39:24.986 --> 01:39:26.503
No, I'm not gonna kill it.
They'll see you.

01:39:26.505 --> 01:39:29.220
They'll see what I want them,
to see!

01:39:29.222 --> 01:39:31.026
Do you still need the cape?
Yes, Janice.

01:39:32.008 --> 01:39:33.222
I still need the cape.

01:39:33.630 --> 01:39:34.419
Done.

01:39:36.971 --> 01:39:37.779
Now William,

01:39:37.781 --> 01:39:39.462
<i>render my illusion suit.</i>
Alright, hang on.

01:39:39.800 --> 01:39:41.671
<i>The monster was full of drones!
It's crazy!</i>

01:39:41.796 --> 01:39:43.037
There you are.

01:39:46.696 --> 01:39:47.777
Easy.

01:39:52.197 --> 01:39:53.392
Who the hell is that?

01:39:54.989 --> 01:39:56.105
Ned!
Happy!

01:39:56.963 --> 01:39:58.956
I got to get you guys out of here!
Get on the jet!

01:39:58.958 --> 01:40:00.924
Who are you?
I work with Spider-Man, ok?

01:40:00.926 --> 01:40:02.740
You got to get on that jet.
You work for Spider-Man?

01:40:03.045 --> 01:40:04.922
I work with Spider-Man,
not for Spider-Man.

01:40:08.336 --> 01:40:10.328
New plan. Into the Tower.
What?

01:40:10.771 --> 01:40:13.380
Happy, are you ok?
<i>Yeah, we're ok. Just get Beck.</i>

01:40:13.598 --> 01:40:15.833
EDITH, target Spider-Man.
<i>Copy.</i>

01:40:20.640 --> 01:40:22.275
I'll just kill the kids myself.

01:40:37.156 --> 01:40:38.522
There you are.

01:40:41.203 --> 01:40:42.681
Into the Crown Jewels vault!

01:40:42.703 --> 01:40:44.842
Yeah, go, go, go!
Come on.

01:40:48.543 --> 01:40:51.135
Go! Into the vault!
The walls are 8 feet thick.

01:40:51.137 --> 01:40:52.253
Go into the vault!

01:40:52.255 --> 01:40:53.986
What?
Into the vault. Go!

01:40:56.592 --> 01:40:57.592
Take cover!

01:41:16.696 --> 01:41:17.696
Ok.

01:41:22.410 --> 01:41:23.410
Yeah?

01:41:23.703 --> 01:41:25.194
No. No.

01:41:29.559 --> 01:41:30.845
I see you.

01:41:32.962 --> 01:41:33.962
Get that thing out...

01:41:39.510 --> 01:41:40.671
Go!

01:41:47.681 --> 01:41:49.138
How does Cap do that?

01:41:59.100 --> 01:42:02.155
Happy, say something, please,
to let me know you're alive!

01:42:02.241 --> 01:42:03.450
<i>I'm here. I'm here.</i>

01:42:03.529 --> 01:42:04.606
Happy, thank God.

01:42:04.720 --> 01:42:06.211
I bought us some time.

01:42:07.747 --> 01:42:09.534
But not much.
<i>I'm trying to get to Beck,</i>

01:42:09.624 --> 01:42:11.286
but I can't shake these drones!

01:42:26.182 --> 01:42:27.182
Gotcha.

01:42:49.413 --> 01:42:50.574
Going up!

01:43:27.660 --> 01:43:28.992
Finally.

01:43:29.078 --> 01:43:32.517
Hey, William, how we doing?
Illusion almost back up.

01:43:33.165 --> 01:43:34.872
<i>I don't know
how you're gonna spin this.</i>

01:43:50.057 --> 01:43:51.343
Great. No webs.

01:44:05.069 --> 01:44:07.311
Are we gonna die?
Nobody dies on my watch.

01:44:09.952 --> 01:44:12.880
I wasted my life playing video games,
and we're gonna die.

01:44:13.791 --> 01:44:16.784
I have a fake ID,
and I've never even used it.

01:44:17.571 --> 01:44:20.234
I post stupid videos daily
for people to like me.

01:44:20.254 --> 01:44:20.890
Hey,

01:44:21.430 --> 01:44:22.872
if it wasn't for
those stupid videos,

01:44:23.273 --> 01:44:24.631
Spider-Man would have
never found you.

01:44:25.754 --> 01:44:27.203
Spider-Man?
Spider-Man follows me?

01:44:28.003 --> 01:44:28.916
I saved us, guys.

01:44:28.929 --> 01:44:30.636
If you saved us,
why are we about to die?

01:44:30.723 --> 01:44:32.134
MJ!
Stop it!

01:44:32.224 --> 01:44:33.590
I'm sorry, ok?

01:44:33.762 --> 01:44:36.831
I'm just. I'm obsessed with telling the truth
even if it hurts other people's feelings.

01:44:38.022 --> 01:44:39.888
I'm in love with Spider-Man's aunt.

01:44:44.354 --> 01:44:45.370
We're sharing, right?

01:45:24.896 --> 01:45:26.263
Your lies are over, Beck.

01:45:27.610 --> 01:45:29.591
This certainly isn't ideal but...

01:45:29.593 --> 01:45:30.940
I have contingencies.

01:45:31.033 --> 01:45:31.863
EDITH?

01:45:40.349 --> 01:45:42.000
Just give me the glasses.

01:45:42.795 --> 01:45:43.911
You want these?

01:45:46.168 --> 01:45:47.168
Come and get them.

01:45:57.184 --> 01:45:58.720
Come on, Peter-tingle.

01:46:23.460 --> 01:46:24.962
Why aren't these drones firing?

01:46:24.964 --> 01:46:26.078
<i>You're in the strike zone.</i>

01:46:26.171 --> 01:46:30.962
<i>The chance of getting hit is...</i>
No, fire all the drones now!

01:46:49.463 --> 01:46:50.197
Beck!

01:46:54.699 --> 01:46:55.411
Beck.

01:46:56.368 --> 01:46:57.652
You lied to me.

01:46:58.623 --> 01:46:59.767
I trusted you.

01:47:00.153 --> 01:47:01.082
I know.

01:47:01.358 --> 01:47:02.615
That's the most...

